title: guy_(genshin_impact)
body:
An NPC from [[Genshin Impact]], he is a member of the Knights of Favonius who guards Mondstadt's northern side gate. He is the son of [[Tunner (genshin impact)|]], a [[farmer]] for the Dawn Winery. Dreaming of becoming a knight, his father spent alot of money for his training to provide him with a better future.

Guy has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. He wears the standard Knights of Favonius uniform, consisting of a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[black shirt]], [[black gloves]], [[vambraces]], [[pauldrons]], a [[breastplate]], a [[brown belt]], [[black pants]], a [[thigh strap]] on his left leg and a pair of [[armored boots|armored]] [[knee boots]]. He also carries a [[sword]] and [[sheath]] by his left leg.

h4. See also

* [[Knight of Favonius (genshin impact)|]]

title: metal_harbor
body:
Metal Harbor is the fourth stage of the Hero story in [[Sonic Adventure 2]] and Sonic Adventure 2: Battle and is playable as Sonic the Hedgehog. As the name suggests, it is a large military harbor belonging to G.U.N, and consists of many shipping yards and aircraft carriers scattered around the area.

Unsurprisingly, the construction of the harbor leads to an abundance of Rails, all of which can be grinded upon. As Sonic races through this level, he encounters many G.U.N. robots trying to stop him from escaping, as well as fighter jets. The harbor also contains several missile launching platforms and aircraft carriers.

title: heterochromia
body:
Wasei-eigo: odd eye

Refers to a pair of eyes with different colored irises. [b]Heterochromia[/b] comes from the Greek ἕτερος ([i]heteros[/i], different) and χρῶμα ([i]chroma[/i], color).

This tag usually refers to [b]complete heterochromia iridum[/b] (both irises have a different coloration). For subjects with partial heterochromia (different colors are present within the iris of a single eye), use [[multicolored eyes]].

Generally, include any [[tag_group:eyes_tags|eye-color tags]] for each instance. Don't use the [[multicolored eyes]] tag unless one or both individual eyes have more than one color.

h4. See also

* [[Mismatched sclera]]
* [[Mismatched pupils]]
* [[Mismatched irises]]
* [[No heterochromia]]
* [[Tag group:eyes tags]]

h4. External links

* Pixiv Encyclopedia: "オッドアイ":http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E3%82%AA%E3%83%83%E3%83%89%E3%82%A2%E3%82%A4 (Odd Eye)
* "Heterochromia iridum":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heterochromia_iridum (Wikipedia article)

title: shalltear_bloodfallen
body:
Character from the series [[overlord_(maruyama)|Overlord by Maruyama]]. She is a [[vampire]] with [[red eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] with [[swept bangs]] and tied in a [[ponytail]]. Wears a [[long dress|long]] [[purple dress]] and a [[hair bow]]. She is one of the floor guardians protecting the Great Tomb of Nazarick. Shalltear is vicious and extremely powerful, as well as in love with [[Ainz Ooal Gown]]. Nicknamed "The Bloody Valkyrie" due to the fact that she is both a vampire and a valkyrie at the same time and thus combines the advantages of both in battle.

Note: Shalltear pads her chest, so the chest size she is usually depicted with is a result of padding.

h4. External links

* "Overlord Wiki: Shalltear Bloodfallen":https://overlordmaruyama.fandom.com/wiki/Shalltear_Bloodfallen

[b]The Boondock Saints[/b] is a 1999 American vigilante action thriller film written and directed by Troy Duffy. title: seed_sr.
body:
A character from [[Zenless Zone Zero]], he is an [[mecha|intelligent construct]] who is a member of the Obol Squad and it's original artillerist. 

Seed Sr. likes [[gardening]] and can often be seen tending to [[flower]]s in his spare time. Despite being an intelligent construct, Seed Sr. always wished to prove he has a heart. One day after he was dispatched to investigate [[hollow (zenless zone zero)|Hollow Zero]] for a mission, he would find an [[Seed (zenless zone zero)|orphaned girl]] with barely any signs of corruption. Taking her in and naming her "Flora", Seed Sr. raised her to prove they both have a heart. [spoilers]Seed Sr. is currently "asleep". Him tampering with his logic core, such as when he fought back against his own self-defense system to avoid harming Seed, slowly caused him to pass away[/spoilers].

Voiced by [[Genda Tesshou]] in Japanese and Zhao Zihan in Chinese.

h4. Appearance

title: huntrix

title: worldwide_miku
body:
The mid-2024 art trend of drawing [[Hatsune Miku]] in different countries' clothing, whether it be urban casual or traditional, or otherwise representing something in the world, no matter what or when.

It gained traction as a Twitter trend following the viral boom of [[Brazilian Miku]], posted on August 17th 2024, and quickly began to expand in scope beyond that initial template, first going beyond urban casual to encompass traditional clothes, then regional subdivisions of countries, nations without countries, historical countries, subcultures, fictional nations and worlds, prehistoric beings, and so on, until she became Everything Miku. This tag also includes posts which reference the trend specifically too, ex. post #8055554 and post #8063674, instances of other vocal synth characters having this trend applied to them such as Teto, and sub-trends developed out of this trend, such as in January 2025 with [[Argentinian Miku]].

title: noh_mask
body:
A traditional Japanese theater [[mask]].

[i]Noh[/i] (能) is a classical Japanese form of dance drama. Noh masks are also used in Kyōgen performances (the comedic counterpart to [i]Noh[/i]) and sometimes also in other Japanese performing arts and ceremonies.

Noh masks are traditionally made from carved cypress wood, painted or lacquered. They are frequently affixed by means of a red silk tying cord. They tend to employ heavy emphasis of shadows in order to portray different emotions (which can be changed by angling the mask).

Masks depicting human beings tend to reflect traditional medieval Japanese aesthetics (resembling characters from woodcut prints), having pale 'chubby' faces with well defined brows and cheek lines, plus prominent eyebrows. Masks depicting older humans tend to have extensive wrinkles and beards.

Masks depicting supernatural entities tend to have large eyes and exaggerated expressions. They may also have horns, fangs and other nonhuman features. Gold paint is frequently used to (literally) highlight the otherworldly appearance of such entities.

Noh masks are used to portray different characters when on stage, similar to Western makeup. An actor may, however, rapidly switch between different masks to fulfill different roles.

h4. Examples

* !post #6019523: [[Hannya]] (Female Demon)
* !post #2511142: [[Hyottoko mask]] (Fire God) 
* !post #1445203: [[Ko-omote mask]] (Young Woman) 
* !asset #23898113: [[Okina mask]] (Old Man)
* !post #1476066: [[Monkey mask]] (Saru/Monkey Spirit)

title: imadake_dabuchi_tabemi
body:
A character introduced by [[McDonald's]] Japan to promote their limited edition Double Cheeseburger, sold from late October to November 2024. Her name most literally means "Try the Double Cheeseburger right now only", with the suffix 美 ([i]mi[/i], Eng: Beautiful) being a common feminine name component in Japan.

She has [[short_hair|short]] [[brown hair]] styled in [[twintails]] and wears a [[red_hat|red]] [[visor cap]] with a large [[McDonald's]] logo visible from the front that's adorned with a [[headset]] and [[microphone]].

Her outfit is based on the old [[fast_food_uniform|McDonalds uniform]] from the 1990s featuring a [[white shirt]] with red [[vertical-striped_shirt|vertical stripes]], topped off with a [[yellow happi]] with a bright red hem, which is secured with a red [[tasuki]] that's tied off into a large [[back_bow|bow on her back]].

Some further accents of her outfit are a [[black necktie]] with [[tie clip|tie clips]], two [[black wristband|black wristbands]], and a black [[button badge]] with the 今 kanji ([i]ima[/i], Eng: Now) which is the first syllable of her name.

Her bottom half consists of [[black shorts]], [[white socks]], and [[red footwear|red]] [[sneakers]] with [[velcro_footwear|velcro]] fasteners.

title: feet
body:
When one or both of a character's feet are prominently displayed or detailed. Add [[foot focus]] when the feet are the main subject or focus of the image.

This does [b]not[/b] include feet fully covered by [[shoes]]. Feet covered by [[sandals]], [[socks]], [[thighhighs]], or [[pantyhose]] still count.


h4. Related tags

h6. Parts

* !post #4905014: [[barefoot]]
* !post #7325645: [[no shoes]]
* !post #7335528: [[soles]]
* !post #9089292: [[toes]]
* !post #7108430: [[toenails]]

h6. Poses / Views

* !post #5453424: [[arched soles]]: A character's feet are positioned in such a way that the plantar (the bottom of the foot) is arched rather than straight.
* !post #8669286: [[between toes]]: Something (e.g. hair, a knife, a pencil, etc.) is between the toes of someone.
* !post #7072954: [[dorsiflexion]]: Flexing of the foot or toes in an upward direction, toward the shin.
* !post #9428414: [[feet only]]
* !post #6588263: [[foot dangle]]: Sitting with the feet hanging freely rather than being raised up or resting on a solid surface.
* !post #8353198: [[pigeon-toed]]: Toes point inwards when standing, sitting, or walking.
* !post #6954452: [[plantar flexion]]: Movement of the foot in which the toes point downward, creating a straighter line from the lower leg to the toes of the foot.
* !post #7665609: [[foot focus]]: When a character's foot or feet are the main subject or focus of the image, especially when the feet are close to the camera or being presented to the viewer.
* !post #4122132: [[soaking feet]]: Sitting or resting with one or both feet in the water (or another liquid).
* !post #9697472: [[spread toes]]: When an image shows feet with the toes spread apart, either by themselves (i.e. flexing your toes apart) or through external means (e.g. moving them apart using hands, placing fingers between them).
* !post #7650001: [[tiptoes]]:Maintaining one's balance on the ends of one's toes. Usually done standing but can be done in other positions as well. 
* !post #5365024: [[the pose]]: When a character lies flat on their stomach with their feet up in the air. This is usually done to show off a character's breasts, ass, and feet all at the same time.
* !post #7594920: [[toe scrunch]]: A character squeezing their toes downward so they appear curled.
* !post #4891849: [[wiggling toes]]: A person moving their toes up, down and side to side with small rapid movements.

h6. Actions / Fetishes

* !post #8927437: [[dirty feet]]: When the feet and/or soles are covered in dirt or dust, usually from going barefoot.
* !post #7711426: [[holding with feet]]: Holding something with the feet. It may or may not be between toes.
* !post #7966085: [[kissing foot]]: Kissing someone's foot.
* !post #9422285: [[licking foot]]: Licking the feet of another character.
* !post #5169783: [[smelling feet]]: Smelling feet.
* !post #8634544: [[tickling feet]]: Tickling someone's feet.
* !post #7386077: [[foot worship]]: Revering the feet of another, usually in a bdsm or femdom context.
* !post #8177384: [[footjob]]: Stimulating a penis with the feet. The equivalent of a handjob, but with the feet. It can be done with bare feet, in socks, or in hosiery.
* !post #8232012: [[double footjob]]: One person simultaneously performing two footjobs on two different people.
* !post #9327629: [[cooperative footjob]]: Multiple people simultaneously performing a footjob on a single person.
* !post #9465772: [[implied footjob]]: When a footjob is being performed (or about to be performed), but the penis isn't visible or the act is hidden from view.
* !post #8703389: [[stepped on]]: For when a character is stepping on another character. Usually signifies dominance over another, or showing who the victor is after a fight.
* !post #5628647: [[trample]]: When a girl or group of girls step, stand, or walk all over a prone victim, usually male. Usually done with bare feet, or socks or stockings. Occasionally done in shoes or sandals. If done in boots or high heeled shoes, it is closely related to BDSM.
* !post #7650987: [[foot pussy]]: Feet simulating a vaginal opening, usually by being held sole to sole. Typically in an inviting manner from a pov perspective.
* !post #8222254: [[toe cleavage]]: Where a character's shoes partially reveal their toes
* !post #3772336: [[painting toenails]] 

h6. Clothing / Accessories

* !post #6036603: [[anklet]]: A piece of jewelry, resembling a bangle or bracelet, but worn around the ankle.
* !post #8670566: [[toeless legwear]]: Legwear that covers the foot while leaving the toes uncovered
* !post #7086442: [[stirrup legwear]]: Legwear that have a stirrup around the sole of the foot, leaving both the toes and heel uncovered.
* !post #5572628: [[bridal legwear]]: Legwear that leave the heel and toes uncovered with the fabric terminating at a ring/loop around the base of the second or third toe
* !post #9348353: [[toe ring]]: A ring that is worn on the toes instead of fingers.

title: nishikigi_chisato
body:
A character in [[Lycoris Recoil]] and said to be the strongest Lycoris of all time.

She has [[red eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] to [[white hair]] stylized in a [[bob cut]] with [[bangs]]. She wears a [[red ribbon|red]] [[hair ribbon]] and the [[lycoris uniform]] that consists of a [[two-tone dress|two-tone]] [[red dress|red]] & [[grey dress|grey]] [[pleated dress]], [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]] with a [[blue ribbon|blue]] [[neck ribbon]], and a [[red belt]].

Her cafe attire, where she works as a [[waitress]], consists of a [[red kimono]], [[green bow|green]] [[waist bow]], and an [[apron]].

Usually depicting [[holding gun|holding a gun]] with [[trigger discipline]], and an [[Heart|Artificial Heart]]. Seems to be a devotee of the [[center axis relock stance]].

She is voiced by [[Anzai Chika]].

h4. See Also

title: dragon_quest_viii
body:
The eighth game in the [i][[Dragon Quest]][/i] series, originally released in 2004 for the [[Playstation 2]] and later brought to North America in 2005 and Europe in 2006. In 2013 it was ported as an app for Android and iOS mobile phones.

It was the first game in the series to be released in America [i]Dragon Quest[/i] title, and the first to be released in Europe at all.

h4. Playable Characters

* [[Hero (DQ8)|Hero]]
* [[Jessica Albert]]

title: pillowdear
body:
An English-speaking [[indie virtual youtuber|Indie]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] who loves to make ASMR videos and stream.

Originally, she had debuted as a cupid here to spread love but later rebranded towards being a dream entity that enjoys helping people sleep. It's important to note that all costumes were designed and drawn by herself.

She still follows a cupid motif featuring [[head wings]] that are [[feathered wings|feathered]], [[pink eyes]] with [[heart-shaped pupils]], and a heart-shaped [[birthmark]] on her left thigh. Her hair is [[very long hair|very long]], reaching down to her feet and typically styled in [[twin braids]]. Her [[two-tone]] hair is pink on the exterior and white on the interior.

title: 28_days_later
body:
A 2002 British movie about a zombie apocalypse in the UK spreading after animal activists free monkeys infected with the "Rage" virus. Considered to be the popularizer of the modern sub-trend of fast/“rabid” zombies.

Is was later follow with three sequels:

* [b]28 Weeks Later[/b] (2007)
28 weeks after the events of the first movie, a NATO task force led by the US Military help rebuild Britain after those infected with the Rage virus died from starvation and British citizens that were away when the outbreak happened return home to rebuild their country. However, the discovery of an asymptomatic carrier of the Rage Virus will led to events of a second outbreak.

* [b]28 Years Later[/b] (2025)
After NATO forces managed to stop the second outbreak from spreading to Europe, NATO puts the whole of Great Britain in indefinite quarantine with shot to kill orders to anyone trying to leave to prevent another outbreak while leaving the survivors to defend themselves alone. 28 years later, a young boy named Spike brings his ill mother Isla to the British mainland to find a Doctor who can cure her, and must face the infected who have gotten stronger and smarter but also other survivors who have gone mad.

* [b]28 Years Later: The Bone Temple[/b] (2026)
An upcoming sequel following the events of 28 Years Later.

title: von_lycaon
body:
A playable character from [[Zenless Zone Zero]], he is a [[wolf boy|wolf thiren]] who is the leader of Victoria Housekeeping Co.

Lycaon is calm, rational and reliable, serving as a versatile attendant and an elegant gentleman. He has a slight obsession with cleanliness, always tidying up his surroundings and takes great care of his [[body fur|fur]]. His canine insticts sometimes shine through when he is particularly happy, as his [[ear wiggle|ears]] and [[tail wagging|tail]] may wag unconsciously, much to his chagrin. [spoilers]Lycaon was previously a student of the [[phantom thief]] [[Jack (zenless zone zero)|]] along with his friend [[Hugo Vlad]]. After Jack's death, the two would form their own phantom thief syndicate named Mockingbird. Sometime later, a misunderstanding concerning Hugo's father's death occured, causing Lycaon to leave Mockingbird and join [[Mayor Mayflower]] to become a member of Victoria Housekeeping, with Hugo deeming him a "traitor".[/spoilers]

Lycaon has [[white fur|white]] [[body fur|fur]], [[short hair|short]] [[white hair]] with [[black hair|black]] [[streaked hair|streaks]] and [[red eyes]]. Being a wolf thiren, he has [[wolf ears]] and a [[fluffy tail|fluffy]] [[wolf tail]] with [[tail belt]]s. He wears a [[white shirt|white]] [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[shirt]] with two [[arm belt]]s, a [[collared vest|collared]] [[grey vest|grey]] [[double-breasted]] [[vest]], [[grey pants]] and [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]]. He has a [[muzzle (mask)|]] on his face, an [[eyepatch]] over his [[one eye covered|right eye]] and keeps a [[pocket watch]] in his [[breast pocket]]. Lycaon also has [[mechanical legs]] connected at the knees, which he uses to perform powerful [[kicking|kicks]] in combat.

Like the other members of Victoria Housekeeping Co. who are based on horror tropes, Lycaon is inspired by [[werewolf|werewolves]], represented by his name and appearance.

Voiced by Will De Renzy-Martin in English (replacing Nicholas Thurkettle (v1.0-v1.6)), [[Kobayashi Chikahiro]] in Japanese and Wang Yuhang in Chinese.

h4. Appearance

h4. See also

h4. External links

title: ruijerd_superdia
body:
Ruijerd Superdia (ルイジェルド・スペルディア) Ruijerd is the former leader of the Superd warrior group, once serving under the demon Laplace with unwavering loyalty. During the Laplace War, the Superd race was cursed through their spears, causing them to lose control and commit atrocities against allies and civilians. This led to the widespread belief that they were savage monsters.

After the Mana Disaster, he meets [[Rudeus Greyrat]] and [[Eris Greyrat]]. Together, they form the party Dead End and join the Adventurer's Guild to earn money and fund their journey back to the Central Continent, with Ruijerd adopting the alias "Watch Dog".

She can deploy her companion [[stuffed wolf|doll]], [[Morte (arknights)|]], to inflict debuff on enemies.

[b]Snoutlet[/b] is a main character from [i][[Mario & Luigi: Brothership]][/i]. He is a flying [[piggy bank]]-like creature who is good friends with [[Connie (mario)|]] and acts as [[Mario]] and [[Luigi]]'s advisor throughout their adventure in Concordia where he resides. title: lois_lane
body:
[b]Lois Lane[/b] is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. Lois is an award-winning journalist for the Metropolis newspaper the [i]Daily Planet[/i] and the primary love interest of the superhero [[Superman]] and his alter ego, [[Clark Kent]].  She is also his wife and the mother of their son, [[Jonathan Kent]], the [[Superboy]] of the DC Rebirth Universe.

Has gained a resurgence in popularity in 2023 thanks to her redesigned appearance in [[My Adventures With Superman]] series, which depicted her as an outgoing [[tan]]-skinned [[tomboy]] instead of her traditional prim and proper [[office lady]] design in the past.

h4.External links
* "Wikipedia: Lois Lane":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lois_Lane

title: freshly-picked_tingle's_rosy_rupeeland
body:
Freshly-Picked Tingle's Rosy Rupeeland is a spin-off game from [[The Legend of Zelda]] series for the [[Nintendo DS]] handheld game console, developed by Vanpool and published by Nintendo. The game was granted a release in PAL format on the 14th of September, 2007 but never received a North American release, due to the unpopularity of [[Tingle]] among western audiences.

It received a Japan only sequel with [[Ripened Tingle's Balloon Trip Of Love]].

title: the_legend_of_zelda
body:
[b]The Legend of Zelda[/b] (ゼルダの伝説, [i]Zelda no Densetsu[/i]) is a high fantasy action-adventure video game series developed and published by [[Nintendo]] and created by the famous game designer [[Miyamoto Shigeru|Shigeru Miyamoto]].

The gameplay consists of a mixture of action, adventure, puzzle solving, role-playing, and occasional platforming, stealth, and racing elements. The series centers around [[Link]], the sole playable character and hero, and is usually set in the land of Hyrule. Link is often given the task of rescuing [[Princess Zelda]] from [[Ganondorf]], the primary villain of the series.

The story commonly involves a relic known as the [[Triforce]], a set of three golden triangles of omnipotence. The hero in each game is not always the same iteration of Link, although the same character sometimes appears across multiple games.

title: 2b_(nier:automata)
body:
The main protagonist of [[NieR:Automata]].

[i]YoRHa No.2 Type B[/i] or 2B is a female-model YoRHa android created to battle the machine lifeforms that have invaded the planet on behalf of the surviving humans. 2B is calm and composed, she does not encourage idle chatter on frivolous subjects and is generally reticent towards others. She also has high respect for the chain of command and rarely questions her orders. However, 2B occasionally expresses a notably sardonic wit in the face of certain situations and can even be hot-headed at times.

Her canonical attire includes a [[two-sided dress|two-sided]] [[black dress]] with [[cleavage cutout|cleavage]] and [[back cutout]]s and [[long sleeves|long]], [[juliet sleeves|juliet]] [[feather-trimmed sleeves]] under which is worn [[white leotard]] which shows off her [[huge ass|ass]]. On her legs she wears [[thighhighs]] [[thighhighs under boots|under]] a pair of [[high heel boots|high heel]] [[thigh boots]]. On her head typically rests a [[black hairband|black]] [[hairband]] on short [[white hair]]. Over her eyes is a black [[blindfold]]. Occasionally throughout the events of the game her blindfold is removed and is thus sometimes [[no blindfold|not included]] by artists. Her eye color is [[blue eyes|blue]], and has a [[mole under mouth|mole under her mouth]].

She has an [[alternate color]]ed appearance in [[Soulcalibur VI]] and [[Final Fantasy XIV]] known as [[2P (nier:automata)|]]. In this appearance she has [[dark skin]], [[black hair]], and white clothes. 2B has made appearances in several other games, including [[Star Ocean: Anamnesis]], [[SINoALICE]], [[Phantasy Star Online 2]], among others.

h4. Appearance

body: Walmart Inc. is a multinational retail corporation that operates a chain of [[Supermarket]]s in the United States and 23 other countries. It is headquartered in Bentonville, Arkansas. title: poor_tom_(jojolion)
body:
Poor Tom is a secondary antagonist featured in the eighth part of the [[Jojo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[JoJolion]].

Poor Tom is a [[Stand (jojo)|]] user whose long-range automatic [[Stand (jojo)|]]  [[Ozon Baby (stand)|]] can manipulate the air pressure in the vicinity.

Poor Tom is a short, overweight man, who can easily be mistaken for a [[child]] due to his height and youthful face. Despite his child-like appearance, Tom is covered in wrinkles and is seen [[smoking]] [[cigarettes]]. His hair is flat with a small bang over his forehead. Most of his hair is notably shaved in a curved shape with short spikes of hair protruding from it, leaving only a small circular patch of hair on the center.

Aside from his [[shorts]] and [[sandals]], a majority of Tom's attire appears to be drawn onto his body with certain parts shaded in. Other drawn-on accessories include a tie with his name on it, a "Coda" pin, referencing the [[Led Zeppelin]] album, and a pocket watch.

He also possesses a [[lab coat|doctor's uniform]] tailored to him, which he wears when working at the TG University Hospital.

Namesake: Poor Tom (Led Zeppelin song)

title: urban_guerrilla_(jojolion)
body:
Urban Guerrilla, otherwise known as Ryo Shimosato, is a secondary antagonist featured in the eighth part of the [[Jojo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[JoJolion]].

He is a [[Stand (jojo)|]] user and can decompose flesh with his [[Brain Storm]].

Urban Guerrilla is a well-built Rock Human, dressed in minimal clothing. He wears a set of [[bracer]]s on his forearms and a pair of [[pants]] with three vents on the thighs and metal knee guards. Over Urban Guerrilla's head is a complex [[hood]] that features a breathing apparatus hooked into his mouth, along with [[goggles]] stylized with six-pronged eyelashes and a lens wiper on the left side.

However, when in public Urban Guerrilla assumes the appearance of a [[lab coat|normal doctor in uniform]] , complete with [[glasses]]. He's also revealed to have [[short hair]].

Urban Guerrilla seems to constantly bare his [[teeth]].

Namesake: Urban Guerrilla (Hawkwind song)

title: doremifasolati_do
body:
Doremifasolati Do is a secondary antagonist featured in the eighth part of the [[Jojo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[JoJolion]].

Doremifasolati Do is a Rock Animal and the pet and means of transportation for [[Urban Guerrilla (Jojolion)|]].

Doremifasolati Do is described as a Rock Animal with a caterpillar-like body. Its face vaguely resembles that of a dog or bear with the tongue constantly sticking out. Its head sports several grooves, having deeper grooves extending from its eye-sockets. The rest of its torso is made up of several flat rectangular stones, adorned with designs resembling human arms. These flat stones provide excellent defense from attacks and can be shifted rapidly like tank treads to mobilize underground.

There are thin appendages covering each side of Doremifasolati Do's face, resembling horse blinders. Beside them, it has spiked circular stones which function as wheels.

Namesake: Doremi Fasol Latido (Hawkwind Album)
other_names: ドレミファソラティ・ド

title: dolomite_(jojolion)
body:
Dolomite, formerly known as Masaji Dorokoma, is a secondary antagonist featured in the eighth part of the [[JoJo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[JoJolion]].
He is a [[Stand (jojo)|]] user and controls people through his [[Blue Hawaii (stand)|]].

Dolomite was originally a normal looking man. Wearing an [[undercut]], the hair on his sides was shaved down whilst the hair on his crown was pulled to the right of his forehead. He wore an exotic striped jacket over a dark, [[long sleeves|long-sleeved shirt]].

After his body was destroyed, Dolomite's appearance drastically changed. His entire body and skin took on a more rock-like appearance, with a rougher complexion and [[cracked skin|cracks in his skin]]. Dolomite's arms and legs are reduced to stumps, on which he wears small round [[piercings]], while his teeth are broken and cracked. His eyes are duller and a strange marking exists above his nose, in the form of a triangle with a small circle above it. His hair has grown out much longer and is unkempt, hanging over his shoulders. As for clothing, he still retains his exotic jacket but nothing else.

Namesake: Dolomites (Italian mountain range) Dolomite (Mineral)

title: wu_tomoki
body:
Wu Tomoki also known as Doctor Wu is a secondary antagonist featured in the eighth part of the [[JoJo No Kimyou Na Bouken]]  series, [[JoJolion]].

Wu Tomoki is a [[Stand (jojo)|]] user who uses his similarly named [[Stand (jojo)|]], [[Doctor Wu (stand)|]], to break his body down into fine particles and enter the bodies of others for both medical uses and in combat.

Despite having a punch perm, Wu Tomoki's hair is straight and primarily consists of small light-colored spheres. He has dark spiked bangs covering the front, with similar tufts of hair outlining the top of his head. His uniform features a long closed jacket with three "DoCToR" name tags on it: two on the front and one on his shoulder.

Namesake: Doctor Wu (Steely Dan song)

She has [[orange eyes]], [[very long hair|long]] [[orange hair]] in [[twintails]] tied by [[pink scrunchie|pink scrunchies]] and wears [[pink thighhighs|pink]] [[polka dot |polka-dot thighhighs]].

h4. External links

* "Yandere Simulator Wiki: Osana Najimi":[https://yandere-simulator.fandom.com/wiki/Osana_Najimi]

title: sakuranbo_(flower_knight_girl)
body:
English Name: Cherry
Artist: [[Takto]]

One of the Flower Knight hailing from a relatively well-off family in Blossom Hill before she lost them in a pest invasion at a young age. Because of this, she treats the player as a father figure.

Not to be confused with [[sakura (flower knight girl)|Sakura]].

title: cernunnos_(fate)
body:

[b]Huge spoilers below for Lostbelt no. 6: Fairy Realm of the Round Table, Avalon le Fay.[/b]

title: monosodium_glutamate
body:
[b]Monosodium Glutamate[/b] or [b]MSG[/b] is a sodium salt of glutamic acid used in cooking as a flavor enhancer with a savory taste that intensifies the umami flavor of food. Created by the [[Ajinomoto]] company, MSG is very popular and used in many Asian countries.

MSG had a negative reputation in the past due to a now discredited theory called “Chinese Restaurant Syndrome” that claimed MSG cause health problems despite many research papers and tests by health officials and experts revealed that MSG is mostly safe to eat with no side effects.

title: loggins_(jojo)
body:
Loggins  is a secondary ally featured in the second part of the [[JoJo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[Battle Tendency]]. As one of [[Lisa Lisa]]'s servants and a fellow [[Hamon]] master, he becomes [[Joseph Joestar (Young)|Joseph]] 's personal trainer after he first encounters the Pillar Men.

Loggins is a tall, [[muscular male]] with chiseled features and somewhat glazed eyes. He wears a large [[tunic]] with two pins on each side, an over-sized fez which is occasionally depicted as leaning to the side, two [[armband]]s on both of his arms and [[baggy pants]].

Namesake: Kenny Loggins (American musician) Loggins and Messina (American pop rock group)

title: messina_(jojo)
body:
Messina is a secondary ally featured in the second part of the [[JoJo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[Battle Tendency]]. As [[Lisa Lisa]]'s servants and Ripple masters, he and Loggins train [[Joseph Joestar (Young)|]] and [[Caesar Anthonio Zeppeli]] in the ways of the [[Hamon]].

Messina is a tall [[muscular male]] with [[short hair]] tied into a [[ponytail]] and a Fu Manchu [[mustache]]. He wears a long hat, a [[sleeveless tunic]], and [[armband]]s. He has very hairy arms, though the hair on his right arm is completely burnt off by Caesar during his training.

Namesake: Jim Messina (American musician), Loggins and Messina (American pop rock group)

title: rio_(blue_archive)
body:

Her full name is Tsukatsuki Rio.

Her firearm is a [[M1911]] pistol.

Has [[very long hair|very long]] [[black hair]] decorated with a single [[hairclip]] and [[ringed eyes|ringed]] [[red eyes]] with [[white pupils]]. Wears a [[white sweater|white]] [[turtleneck sweater]] underneath a [[black jacket|black]] [[blazer]] with a [[id card]]. Also wears a [[pleated skirt]] over [[pantyhose]], a [[holster]] [[thigh strap|strapped]] to her [[thigh holster|thigh]], and [[black shoes|black]] [[high heels]].

She is often seen with a [[tablet PC]].

title: zimmerman_(armored_core_vi)
body:
[b]SG-027 ZIMMERMAN[/b]

A handheld [[shotgun]] for Armored Core [[mecha]]s that appears in [[Armored Core VI: Fires of Rubicon]].
It is infamous for its game-breaking strength in early versions, which was nerfed later on, but still powerful enough to be part of PVP meta.
Japanese players may call them 重ショ, short for 重ショットガン (heavy shotgun).

title: armored_core
body:
Armored Core is a series of games made by [[fromsoftware|FromSoftware]]. It is set in the distant, often [[post-apocalypse|post-apocalyptic]] future where corporations fight, utilizing highly customizable [[mecha]]s called AC (Armored Core) piloted by mercenaries.

The series is notable for depicting [[human]] presence almost entirely by voices, leaving characters' appearance to player's imagination entirely in most games.

title: fishing
body:
As a verb, it is the act of catching [[fish]]. As a noun, fishing refers to the recreational sport. Most examples of fishing on Danbooru are of the type performed with a [[fishing rod]] and baited hook, but methods of fishing vary widely, from fishing with [[net|nets]] to fishing with [[solar gun|solar guns]] and [[harpoon|harpoons]] (spearfishing) to the use of [[explosive|explosives]] (dynamite fishing). Fishing may be done from a [[boat]], from a [[shore]] or [[pier]], or while [[underwater]].

title: father_alvin
body: Minor character in [[Deltarune]]. Son of [[Gerson Boom]] and a pastor of Hometown's church.

title: gerson_boom
body:
A character from [[Undertale]], one of the shopkeepers and the elderly mentor/idol of [[Undyne]].
He is also mentioned in [[Deltarune]] with full name of Gerson Boom, deceased author famous for the book series "Lord of the Hammer" and is [[Father Alvin]]'s father.

[spoiler]He appears in Deltarune Chapter 4, revived from his ashes through the power of a unique Dark Fountain. Here, Gerson is simply referred to as an "old man," with his name only being confirmed in the chapter's epilogue. He serves as the secret boss and Shadow Crystal holder of the same chapter, under the title "Hammer of Justice."[/spoiler]

title: heracles_(fate)
body:

For the [[Fate/Zero]] character, see [[Berserker (Fate/Zero)]].

A [[tall male|colossus]] (over 8 feet) of [[muscular male|muscle]], with [[dark skin|brown skin]], [[glowing eyes]] (one golden, one red) and long wild [[black hair]]. Wears only [[bracelet]]s and an armored kilt, and wields a chipped stone greatsword. Often seen with his Master Illyasviel von Einzbern, who prefers to sit on his shoulder.

body:
New character from [[Tsukihime (Remake)]], first appearing in [i]Tsukihime -A piece of blue glass moon-[/i]

Mio is a middle schooler on the run from her family. Due to her last name Saiki, it is implied that she is a member of the Saiki branch family of the Tohnos and possibly a relative of [[Saiki Gouto]].

She wears black [[shorts]], a gray [[jacket]], [[shorts]], [[thighhighs]] and [[shoes]]. Mio has [[purple hair]] with  [[twintails]]. her eye color is [[grey eyes|grey]].

title: armored_core:_nine_breaker
body:
An game in [[Armored Core]] series, where the player takes on series of trainings to become the "Nine Breaker".

Utilizing same engine as [[Armored Core: Nexus]], it is meant to be a supplement to other 3rd generation games.

title: nine-ball_onyx
body:
A bipedal Armored Core [[mecha]] that appears in [[Armored Core: Nine Breaker]] and serves as the game's mascot.

It is a recreation of the original [[Nineball|Nine-Ball]] made by an anonymous party, using parts from 3rd generation games.
While it is only called Nine-Ball in-game, some merchandises have called it as Nine-Ball Onyx (ナインボール・オニキス).

Nine-Ball Onyx can be distinguished from other Nine-Balls by its CR-C98E2 core part, which has sharper overall shape than the original. Its emblem is also different as Onyx uses stylized number '9' and without a circle around it, which is also seen in the game's logo.

[[Armored Core: Nexus]] has an AC called Baby's Breath, piloted by an AI Code: Crimson, which appearance and weaponry being exactly the same, making them impossible to distinguish from each other.
other_names: ナインボール・オニキス

title: gnosis_(arknights)
body:
[i]Former Karlan Trade Chief Technical Officer, not interested in a single thing beyond technology.[/i]

A playable Supporter Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real Name: Gnosis Edelweiss

Former Chief Technology Officer of Karlan Trade Company, whose family, the Edelweiss, is affiliated with the [[Silverash (arknights)|]] family.

Joined Rhodes Island as an operator via special agreement between Karlan Trade and Rhodes Island.

One of the main characters in the side story [i]Break the Ice[/i].

His motif is based on Red-crowned cranes.

His [[voice actor|voice actors]] are [[Midorikawa Hikaru]] (JP), Flynn Liu (CN-Mandarin), Charles Aitken (EN), and Jun Seung-hwa (KR)

body:

She has [[medium_hair|medium]] [[brown_hair|brown hair]]. Her hairstyle includes [[sidelocks]] and [[short twintails]]. The color of eyes is [[brown eyes|brown]] too. She has a green [[bandaid on nose]]. Usually she is drawn with [[large breasts]], though sometimes with [[medium_breasts|medium]] ones. She is wearing a [[pink_hat|pink]] [[baseball cap]] [[backwards_hat|backwards]], a [[pink hoodie]], [[green overalls]] with the [[frog print]] and pink [[sneakers]]. title: hyaku_shiki
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series.

[b]MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki (Type 100)[/b]

A high-performance Gundam-type [[mobile suit]] that serves as [[Quattro Bajeena]]'s final main personal unit in [[Zeta Gundam]]. Armaments include a [[beam rifle]], clay [[bazooka_(gundam)|bazooka]], and a pair of [[energy sword|beam sabers]]. It has a trademark golden color due to its experimental special and advanced anti-beam coating. The mecha can also use the [[beam_cannon|mega bazooka launcher]].

It is the actual final and definitive version of the MSN-001 [[Delta Gundam]], a prototype transformable Mobile Suit that was scrapped in the planning stages and later changed into a high-performance mobile suit. Vestiges of this can be seen in the flexible binders behind the Hyaku Shiki. 

[spoilers]The Hyaku was severely [[damaged]] in [[battle]] during the final [[duel]] of [[Haman Karn]] (in her [[Qubeley]]) and Quattro Bajeena. Apparently destroyed after Haman defeats Quattro, its [[wreckage]] is later shown floating in space (with its cockpit hatch open), implying Quattro's survival of the encounter. The repaired MS later appears in [[Gundam ZZ]] as part of the [[Argama]]'s [i][[Gundam Team]][/i] where it is operated mostly by [[Beecha Oleg]] and [[Mondo Agake]].[/spoilers]

h4. Related development

The calm and collected chairman of Karlan Trading Company and current patriarch of the Silverash family. He is the oldest of the Silverash siblings, being the older brother of both [[pramanix_(arknights)|Enya "Pramanix" Silverash]] and [[cliffheart_(arknights)|Ensia "Cliffheart" Silverash]]. His choice of weapon is a cane sword. He is also accompanied by his pet bird [[tenzin_(arknights)|Tenzin]], which also acts as his ranged attack.

The fact that he is the last male heir of the Silverash family has lead to a fanart theme depicting him making a huge deal out of the Doctor marrying either of his sisters in order to continue his bloodline, despite not expressing such desires in canon.

Just like his sisters, his motif is based on the snow leopard.

His [[voice actor]]s are [[Konishi Katsuyuki]] (Japanese), Wu Lei (Chinese), James Day (English) and Nam Doh-hyeong (Korean). His art designer is [[Ryuuzaki Ichi]].

title: gundam_gquuuuuux
body:
A 2025 [[science fiction]] and [[mecha]] anime television series produced by [[Studio Khara]] ([[Rebuild of Evangelion]]) and [[Sunrise (company)|]]. It is part of the [[Gundam]] franchise, was directed and produced by [[Anno Hideaki]] and has mechanical designs by [[Yamashita Ikuto]], who created the robots for [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]]. The series has 12 episodes. It also has a compilation film titled [i]Mobile Suit Gundam GQuuuuuuX -Beginning-[/i].

GQuuuuuux takes place in [b]Universal Century 0085[/b] (85 years after the creation of the first permanent colony in [[space]]) in an [[alternate universe|alternative timeline]] where [[Zeon]] successfully captured the [[RX-78-2 Gundam]], which changed the outcome of [[mobile suit gundam|"The One Year War"]] (U.C. 0079).

title: atoferatofe_rybak
body:
Atoferatofe Rybak (アトーフェラトーフェ・ライバック), known as Atofe, is a character from [[Mushoku Tensei]]. She is a powerful immortal Demon Lord, feared for her overwhelming physical strength and regenerative abilities, but notoriously limited in intelligence.

During the war against humanity, Atofe was an ally of Laplace, the Demon God, fighting as one of the most brutal figures in the demon army. She was married to Kalman I, the First North God, and is the mother of Kalman II AKA  [spoiler][[Sandor von grandeur]][/spoiler], who in turn is the father of Kalman III AKA [[Aleksander Ryback]], the current North God. Her lineage is among the most respected in the world of swordsmanship.

Despite her strength, Atofe is incredibly stupid—unable to comprehend complex sentences and prone to violent reactions over occasional misunderstandings. Her impulsiveness and lack of strategy make her unpredictable and dangerous, even to her allies.

She maintains a fierce rivalry with [[Perugius dola]]. Atofe also has a habit of forcibly capturing people and compelling them to become soldiers in her army.

title: mirko
body:
A character from [[Boku no Hero Academia]]. A professional hero with "rabbit" quirk, granting her various rabbit-like abilities such as immensely strong legs, capable of jumping at a great height, and superhuman hearing ability. Her civilian name is [b]Usagiyama Rumi[/b]. 

She is depicted as a [[dark skin|dark skinned]] or [[tan|tanned]], [[toned|athletic]] [[rabbit girl]] (albeit her fanart frequently depicted her with [[muscular female|muscular]] body instead) with [[white hair|white]], [[long hair]]. While under hero duties, she wears a [[white leotard]], which when combined with her organic [[rabbit ears]] and [[rabbit tail|tail]] can make it appears as if she's wearing a [[playboy bunny]] outfit.

Mirko was named after Mirko "Cro Cop" Filipovich, a now retired [[mixed martial arts]] fighter and Kickboxer, best known for competing in [[Pride Fighting Championships]] and the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]].

Due to a localization error, "Mirko" is sometimes inappropriately spelled as "Miruko". When he was fighting in Japan, "Mirko" had to be translated as "Miruko/ミルコ" as Japanese does not have an independent "R" sound (the hiragana らりるれろ are roughly pronounced ra-ri-ru-re-ro). Western manga translators who did not know the reference unintentionally retranslated the faulty original translation.

title: ellen_joe
body:
A playable character from [[Zenless Zone Zero]], she is a [[shark girl|shark thiren]] who is a maid for Victoria Housekeeping Co. and also a high school student.

Ellen has a laid back and aloof personality and is quite popular in school, though she prefers spending time with her friends [[Ruby (zenless zone zero)|]], [[Monna (zenless zone zero)|]] and [[Lynn (zenless zone zero)|]]. She is constantly [[sleepy|tired]] and hate activities that require energy, always carrying [[lollipop]]s to maintain her energy consumption. However, with support of her teammates, Ellen can unleash formidable power during critical moments in battle, albeit at the cost of her energy.

Ellen has [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] with [[red hair|red]] [[colored inner hair]], [[red eyes]], a [[mole]] under her [[mole under eye|left eye]] and on her [[mole on arm|left arm]], [[red nails]] and [[medium breasts|medium]] to [[large breasts]]. Being a shark thiren, she has [[sharp teeth]] and a large [[shark tail]] with a [[scar]] [[scar on tail|on it]] along with [[sticker]]s and [[crossed bandaids]]. She wears a [[maid]] outfit consisting of a [[short dress|short]] [[black dress|black]] [[frilled dress]] with [[puffy short sleeves]], a [[white apron|white]] [[waist apron]], [[black pantyhose]] and a pair of [[black shoes|black]] [[high heels]]. She has a [[maid headdress]] with a [[spiked hairband|spiked]] [[metal hairband]] on her head, [[frilled wrist cuffs|frilled]] [[metal wrist cuffs]], multiple [[hairclip]]s and a [[spiked collar|spiked]] [[metal collar]]. She wields a pair of [[oversized object|large]] [[shears]].

Like the other members of Victoria Housekeeping Co. who are based on horror tropes, Ellen is likely inspired by movies like [[Jaws (Movie)|]] where [[shark]]s are the main antagonist.

Voiced by Giselle Fernandez in English, [[Wakayama Shion]] in Japanese and Xiao Qingyuan in Chinese.

title: corin_wickes
body:
A playable character from [[Zenless Zone Zero]], she is a young girl who is a maid for Victoria Housekeeping Co.

Corin has very low self-esteem and is quite timid, always [[stutter]]ing and apologizing for anything and everything. Despite this, she is one of Victoria Housekeeping's most reliable members and has a flawless performance. Before joining Victoria Housekeeping, Corin was very [[sick]] with a critical illness and had to undergo major surgery which her large [[scar]]s in the process. Though the scars are usually hidden by her outfit, they can be seen in her full [[Mindscape Cinema (zenless zone zero)|]] art.

Corin has [[long hair|long]] [[green hair]] tied into [[twintails]] with bangs hanging [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]], [[hair intakes]] and [[purple eyes]]. She wears a [[maid]] outfit consisting of a [[black dress]] with [[puffy short sleeves]] and is trimmed with blades, a [[white apron|white]] [[frilled apron|frilled]] [[maid apron]], a [[brown belt]] with a large [[wallet chain|chain]], large [[metal wrist cuffs]] and a pair of [[black boots|black]] [[lace-up boots]]. She has a [[maid headdress]] on her head, multiple [[screw hair ornament]]s, [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon]]s and a [[brown bag|brown]] [[bear bag]] on her back. She wields a large [[circular saw]] on a pole, which she has a habit of destroying things with.

Like the other members of Victoria Housekeeping Co. who are based on horror tropes, Corin is inspired by [[Frankenstein's Monster]], represented by her appearance.

Voiced by Chloe Eves in English, [[Igarashi Hiromi]] in Japanese and Mufei in Chinese.

title: alexandrina_sebastiane
body:
A playable character from [[Zenless Zone Zero]], she is head maid for Victoria Housekeeping Co. and it's most senior member. 

Rina possesses a beautiful and mature appearance, always maintaining a noble and professional demeanor, even with the most difficult of clients. However, her bangboo, [[Drusilla (zenless zone zero)|]] may express Rina's true thoughts at times. Despite cooking being her favorite hobby, Rina is quite [[bad food|bad]] at it, with [[Ellen Joe|few]] being capable of consuming her dishes. Frequently accompanied by her [[bangboo (zenless zone zero)|]] [[Anastella (Zenless Zone Zero)|]] and [[Drusilla (Zenless Zone Zero)|]], whom she also wields in combat.

Rina has [[very long hair|very long]] [[low-tied long hair|low-tied]] [[grey hair]] with bangs hanging [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]], [[red eyes]] and [[large breasts]]. She wears a [[maid]] outfit consisting of a [[black dress]] with [[juliet sleeves]] and a long [[side slit]], a [[white apron|white]] [[frilled apron|frilled]] [[maid apron]], [[black gloves|black]] [[partially fingerless gloves]], a [[white pantyhose|white]] [[single leg pantyhose]] with a single [[white socks|white]] [[kneehighs|kneehigh]] on her right leg and a pair of [[black shoes|black]] [[high heels]]. She has a [[maid headdress]] on her head, [[white ribbon|white]] [[hair ribbon]]s, a [[white bowtie]] and numerous [[spikes]] throughout her outfit. Rina also has the ability to [[floating|float]] through electromagnetism, as she has a magnetic generator on her back and multiple electromagnets distributed throughout her outfit. 

Like the other members of Victoria Housekeeping Co. who are based on horror tropes, Rina is inspired by [[ghost]]s and the paranormal, represented by her appearance and ability to float.

Voiced by Morgan Lauré in English (replacing Crystal Lee (v1.0-v1.7)), [[Arai Satomi]] in Japanese and Zhang Ruoyu in Chinese.

title: astra_yao
body:
A playable character from [[Zenless Zone Zero]], she is the leader of the Stars of Lyra who is a very famous and iconic [[singer]] in New Eridu. 

Commonly referred to as "The Queen" when she is on stage, where she maintains a cold and imposing presence. However, Astra is actually a bubbly and outgoing lady who likes to sneak away from work to hang out with [[Wise (zenless zone zero)|Phae]][[Belle (zenless zone zero)|thon]] or meet with fans. Astra is also close friends with her manager and  [[bodyguard]] [[Evelyn Chevalier]], whom she is quite reliant on. Astra was a child when Eridu fell to [[Hollow (zenless zone zero)|Hollow Zero]] and was saved by an H.I.A. squad before they were slain by [[Ethereal (zenless zone zero)|]]s. Whilst at a makeshift shelter, she heard the music of Joran de Winter, melting away the fear and loneliness of her and everyone else. This would inspire Astra to become the new era's songstress.

Astra has [[long hair|long]] [[straight hair|straight]] [[black hair]] with [[hair intakes]], [[cut bangs]], [[red eyes]] and [[large breasts]]. She wears a [[short dress|short]] [[white dress]] with [[white shorts|white]] [[short shorts]] underneath, a [[red shrug]] with [[long sleeves|long]] [[frilled sleeves]], a [[pearl necklace]], [[thigh beads]] on her left leg and a pair of [[black shoes|black]] [[platform heels]] with [[black bow|black]] [[footwear bow|bows]]. She has [[bracelet]]s on her left arm, [[gold earrings]], a gold [[hair ornament]] and a [[white hairband]]. Astra is also commonly depicted wearing [[sunglasses]] as her "disguise". She wields a [[staff]] named "Hemiola", which can act as a [[microphone]].

Voiced by [[Molly Zhang]] in English, [[Endou Aya]] in Japanese and Xiao N in Chinese.

title: evelyn_chevalier
body:
A playable character from [[Zenless Zone Zero]], she is a member of the Stars of Lyra who serves as [[Astra Yao]]'s [[bodyguard]] and manager.

Evelyn is known for being calm, decisive and professional, serving as an irreplacable pillar behind Astra. Though she can be quite [[serious]] and protective, she is notably more relaxed around Astra and the [[Wise (zenless zone zero)|Phae]][[Belle (zenless zone zero)|thon]] siblings. While little is known about Evelyn's childhood, at some point, she was brought into the "Organization" where she was trained to be an [[assassin]]/[[spy]] and performed numerous jobs. The [[hacker]] [[Rain (zenless zone zero)|]] also worked for them and became indebted to Evelyn after she saved Rain's life. Her final job was to work as a spy for the company Fugue under the indentity "Scheele's Green" by becoming the manager of Astra Yao. Evelyn was warmed by Astra's sincerity as a person, gradually opening herself up and eventually cutting ties with the "Organization".

Evelyn has [[blonde hair]] tied into a [[single hair bun]] with a [[bun with braided base|braided base]], [[parted bangs]] that partially [[hair over one eye|covers her left eye]], [[hair intakes]], [[purple eyes]] with a [[mole]] [[mole under eye|under her right eye]] and [[large breasts]]. She wears a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt|white]] [[sleeveless shirt]] with [[see-through cleavage]] and a [[back cutout]], a [[yellow necktie|gold necktie]], a [[two-sided jacket|two-sided]] [[black jacket]] [[jacket on shoulders|on her shoulders]], [[tight pants|tight]] [[black pants|black]] [[high-waist pants|high-waist]] [[latex pants]], [[uneven gloves|uneven]] [[two-tone gloves|two-tone]] [[black gloves|black]] and [[red gloves]], an [[o-ring thigh strap]] on her right leg and a pair of [[black boots|black]] [[high heel boots]]. She also has multiple [[butterfly hair ornament]]s and a [[ring hair ornament]] in her hair, an [[earpiece]] in her right ear, a [[black choker]] and a [[chest harness]]. She wields a [[knife]] named "Lunalux Garrote" in combat.

Voiced by [[Elizabeth Maxwell]] in English, [[Hikasa Youko]] in Japanese and Li Chanfei in Chinese.

title: lobotomy_corporation_(identity)_(project_moon)
body:
[[list of project moon Identities|Identities]] of [[Limbus Company]] Sinners extracted from mirror worlds where they joined the [[Lobotomy Corporation]] as [[employee (project moon)|employees]] during the events of that game. They are exclusive to the Walpurgisnacht banners and can only be obtained through extraction/the dispenser during those times.

Each one has the title of Lobotomy E.G.O and use the [[E.G.O_(project moon)|E.G.O equipment]] of an abnormality. The title is partially shared with [[Technology Liberation Alliance (identity) (project moon)|Technology Liberation Alliance identities]], but exclusively utilize E.G.O equipment first introduced in [[Lobotomy Corporation]].
* Faust's identity is based on a [[Malkuth (project moon)|Control Team]] captain using the [[regret_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Forsaken Murderer]].
* Don Quixote's first identity is based on a [[Hod (project moon)|Training Team]] agent using the [[lantern_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Meat Lantern (project moon)|]]. However, she is also equipped with the E.G.O gifts from [[Void Dream]] and [[Fragment of the Universe]].
* Outis' identity is based on a [[Hod (project moon)|Training Team]] captain using the [[magic_bullet_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Der Freischuetz (project moon)|Der Freischütz]].
* Yi Sang's identity is based on a [[Netzach (project moon)|Safety Team]] agent using the [[solemn_lament_(e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Funeral of the Dead Butterflies]].
* Ryoshu's identity is based on both a [[Netzach (project moon)|Safety Team]] captain [spoiler]and the [[Gebura (project moon)|Red Mist]][/spoiler] [[asymmetrical dual wielding|dual wielding]] [[Red Eyes (e.g.o)|]] and [[Penitence (e.g.o)|]] from [[Spider Bud]] and [[One Sin and Hundreds of Good Deeds]] respectively. 
* Don Quixote's second identity is based on a [[Tiphereth A (Project Moon)|Central Command Team]] captain using the [[in the name of love and hate (e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Queen Of Hatred]].
* Rodion's identity is based on a [[Chesed (Project Moon)|Welfare Team]] agent using the [[the sword sharpened with tears (e.g.o)|E.G.O equipment]] of [[Knight Of Despair]].

title: list_of_project_moon_identities
body:
Introduced in [[Leviathan (Project Moon)|]] and expanded upon within [[Limbus Company]], Identities are alternate forms of individuals from Mirror Worlds accessed by Mirror technology.

When using an Identity, the individual gains the equipment, skills, and personality of that identity. Limbus Company makes extensive use of this, allowing the Sinners to utilize different Mirror Worlds to their advantage in combat. 

Young-ji initially invented the Glass Window, which was further refined by [[Yi Sang (project moon)|]] into the Mirror. After the League of Nine Littérateurs collapsed, the remaining members spread out throughout the City with the Mirror technology. The technology quickly came into possession of the Wings, syndicates, and other groups of the City who began researching, experimenting and improving upon it.

[spoiler]As shown by [[Erlking Heathcliff (Project Moon)|]], Identities of different people can be either willingly or forcibly imposed onto others regardless of whether or not that Identity actually belongs to them.[/spoiler]

All Identity artwork is sourced from the unofficial "Limbus Company - Organized Assets":https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1Nk9WWMxEcovs5Ewku5ICT1PbfByNcV_z Google Drive.

title: liu_association_south_uniform
body:
[[list of project moon Identities|Identities]] of [[Limbus Company]] Sinners extracted from mirror worlds where they joined the Liu Association, the 6th of the twelve Fixer Associations of the City.

They specialize in group combat situations and primarily use [[martial arts]] while equipped with [[gauntlets]] that allow them to start [[fire|fires]] when striking a target. They all wear [[chinese clothes|Chinese-inspired attire]], and the standard uniform consists of a [[black vest]] with a [[red necktie]] fastened with a gold [[tie clip]] and [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]] underneath. Higher-ranking section members also wear [[red coat|red coats]].

No identities are based on any specific characters as of this time.

title: mori_calliope_(rock_bunny)
body:
The 9th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive English|hololive EN]]'s [[Mori Calliope]].

It is a rock themed outfit consisting of an [[off shoulder]] [[fur-trimmed jacket]] over a [[strapless]] [[black bustier]], [[black shorts]], [[torn leggings]] and [[black boots]]. She also has [[headphones around neck|headphones around her neck]] along with a [[studded choker|studded]] [[black choker]], and can wear either a [[rabbit ear hairband]] or [[Tutu (mori calliope)|]] on her head as an accessory.

She has 3 different [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyles]] for this costume:

title: peacoat
body:
A type of outer [[jacket]] or [[coat]], generally made heavy wool. Pea coats are characterized by short length, broad [[lapels]], [[double-breasted]] fronts, often large wooden, metal or plastic buttons, three or four in two rows, and vertical or slash [[pocket]]s. References to the pea jacket appear in American [[newspaper]]s at least as early as the 1720s, and modern renditions still maintain the original design and composition.

It was originally worn (navy blue colour) by sailors of European and later American navies. A pea coat that extends to the thighs is called "bridge coat", and is a [[military uniform|uniform]] exclusively for officers and military chief petty officers. Only officers wear ones with [[epaulettes]].

Peacoat is mostly a misnomer, by the  danbooru coat guidelines of coat and jacket. On danbooru a jacket is from waist to hip length, and coat is thigh or lower. Peacoats are characterized by their short length, reaching the hips or crotch, which would be considered a [[jacket]]. 

h4. Examples
* !post #621272

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Pea coat":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pea_coat]

title: overalls
body:
A garment originally used as protective clothing. It consists of a bib, [[suspenders]], and an attached lower garment, such as [[pants]], shorts or skirt. It is usually made of blue [[denim]] and worn either with shirts or with [[naked overalls|nothing underneath]].

Not to be confused with [[suspender pants]], [[suspender shorts]] and [[suspender skirt]].

title: nijisanji_idol_uniform
body:
A standardized concert [[idol clothes|idol uniform]] for [[Nijisanji]], as seen in post #7374894, designed by [[Iwamoto Zerogo]]. First introduced in 2021 with the announcement of the [i]Nijisanji 4th Anniversary LIVE 「FANTASIA」[/i] and primarily associated with such large anniversary concerts, though it also gets used at smaller events.

It is mostly white and dark blue/black with [[gold trim]]. Each member's version of the uniform is made from one of six top and one of six bottom parts (three each for boys and girls), with a personalized accent color plus some unique elements (e.g. [[Tsukino Mito]]'s [[rabbit ear headphones]]).

title: odda_(arknights)
body:
[i]Odda, Messenger from Kazdel, bearing greetings from friends lost to time.[/i]

A playable Guard Operator in [[Arknights]].

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]
[tbody]
      [tr][td]Place of Birth:[/td]
      [td]Kazdel[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Birthday:[/td]
      [td]January 1[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Race:[/td]
      [td]Sarkaz[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Height:[/td]
      [td]168 cm[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Combat Experience:[/td]
      [td]18 years[/td][/tr]
  [/tbody]
[/table]
[/expand]

A former member of Babel, now works as an informant and Messenger between Kazdel and Rhodes Island.

He is short and baby-faced, with a weaker constitution compared to other Sarkaz due to some injuries he sustained as a child.

His weapon of choice is a hammer repurposed from an engine cylinder of an abandoned vehicle. Both of this weapon and his name belonged to his mother, a doctor of Babel, which he inherited when she passed away.

His [[voice actor]]s are Asari Ryōta (Japanese), Yu Songtao (Chinese), Ry McKeand (English) and Han Man-joong (Korean). His illustrator is [[scorpion5050]].

title: mario
body:
[b]Mario[/b] ([b]マリオ[/b]) is the main protagonist of the [[mario (series)|Mario series]], the legendary mascot of [[Nintendo]], and basically the video game equivalent of [[Mickey Mouse]]. 

Mario is normally a [[plumber]], but in games, he uses his legendary [[jumping]] and combat abilities to defend the inhabitants of the usually peaceful Mushroom World from power-hungry villains such as [[Bowser]]. During most of his adventures, he often teams up with his brother [[Luigi]] and their partner [[Yoshi]] for extra support, as they are the only two characters he fully trusts to help him. When not adventuring, Mario participates in a variety of [[playing sports|sporting events]] and even works as one of his alter-egos, [[Dr. Mario]]. 

h4. Official Art

* !post #7952707

title: miyu_edelfelt
body:
One of the main characters in [[Fate/kaleid liner PRISMA ILLYA]], partnering with the [[kaleidostick]] [[Magical Sapphire]].

She was born as [[Sakatsuki Miyu]], the child of God from a parallel world, serving a similar tole to [[Illyasviel von Einzbern]]'s original role as the [[Holy Grail (fate)|]]. After the fourth Holy Grail War in that world, she was discovered by [[Emiya Shirou (prisma illya)|]] and was adopted by [[Emiya Kiritsugu]] to use as a tool, becoming Shirou's adoptive sister. A decade later after the fifth Holy Grail War, she was sent to Illya's world via Shirou's wish on the Holy Grail along with the [[class card (prisma illya)|]]s. [[Luviagelita Edelfelt]] adopts her as her younger sister due to her ongoing rivalry with [[Tohsaka Rin]].

She was introduced as a Caster-class servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]] during the rerun of the [[Mahou Shoujo Kikou ~Prisma Codes~]] event.

title: ryougi_shiki
body:
Ryougi Shiki is one of the main protagonists of the [[Kara no Kyoukai]] novels. She is a teenage girl who possesses the [[Mystic Eyes of Death Perception]], a supernatural ability that allows the user to see the inherent mortality of everything (both living and non-living) in the form of lines.

She has short [[brown hair]] and [[brown eyes]]. She is usually seen wearing a [[red jacket|red]] [[leather jacket]] over a [[blue kimono]]. When she uses her powers, her eyes [[glowing eyes|glow]] an iridescent [[blue eyes|blue]] (though she is sometimes illustrated with blue eyes while [i]not[/i] using her powers [[artistic error|by mistake]]).

During the [[Fate/Grand Order]] collaboration event with Kara no Kyoukai, she can be acquired as an Assassin-class Servant.

[spoiler]Her [[Void Shiki|third personality]] (aka the embodiment of the Void) can also be summoned as a Saber-class Servant. This version of hers wields the Kanesada Kuji, and as she gains power, her hair grows out, her kimono grows more elaborate, and has the Mystic Eyes of Death Perception activated permanently.[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Sakamoto Maaya]]

title: roon_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the German heavy cruiser [i]Roon[/i], as part of a collaboration with [[World of Warships]]. 
Character design by [[Terras]], voiced by [[Satou Satomi]]. 

She has [[blonde_hair|blonde hair]] and [[brown_eyes|brown eyes]], with [[large breasts]]. Her default outfit consists of an [[open jacket|open]] [[black jacket]], [[black shirt|black]] [[double-breasted]] [[collared shirt]] with an [[Iron Cross]] medal, [[black skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt]], and black [[knee boots]]. 

Her [[rigging]] is emblazoned with some white [[Iron Cross]]es and a black-white stripe pattern. It consists of animalistic hull pieces holding her two triple and two twin 203 mm mounts, her intended armament, plus various 105 mm [[anti-aircraft gun]]s and [[searchlight]]s.

Her looks hide a highly-sinister personality. Similar to [[graf_zeppelin_(azur_lane)|Graf Zeppelin]], Roon is sadistic, relishing in bloodshed against her enemies, and even expresses willingness to attack her own allies. She becomes rather [[yandere]] for the Commander with enough affection, and will eagerly kill anyone who attempts to come between the two. 

Roon has the "Expert Loader" skill, based on the [[World of Warships]] skill of the same name. It allows her to change shell types between high explosive and armor-piercing on the fly.

The historical Roon never saw much in the way of development, and no ship of her class was even considered, ordered, or laid down. The concept was largely based on a triple 8" turret designed by the [i]Kriegsmarine[/i].

title: shiki_eiki
body:
The "Highest Judge of Paradise", final boss and a playable character of [[Touhou]]'s [[Phantasmagoria of Flower View]].

A "yama":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yama responsible for judging the souls of the dead, having the ability to identify good and evil. She is best known, however, for being quite moralistic and calling out other characters on their faults - more so (sometimes with physical punishment) upon her errant shinigami, [[Onozuka Komachi]]. Based on her illustration from "The Grimoire of Marisa", fanworks often comically depict her as rather petite and [[flat chest|flat-chested]] compared to her imposing, busty employee - something which angers Eiki - though a full-figured woman with long legs and [[zettai ryouiki]] is another depiction often used in fanart. Canon is inconsistent on which form is true, with some speculation that the child depiction is used as an alternate form for reasons unknown.

Yamaxanadu (ヤマザナドゥ) is her title (meaning "Yama of Paradise"), but has led fans to erroneously read her name as "Shikieiki Yamaxanadu". In actuality, her given name is Eiki and her surname is Shiki.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[green hair]] often cut [[asymmetrical hair|asymmetrically]] and either [[blue eyes|blue]] or [[green eyes]]. Her outfit is a [[frilled hat|frilled]] [[blue hat]], a [[blue vest]] with [[buttons]] and a [[ribbon-trimmed vest|ribbon trim]] and [[epaulettes]], a [[white shirt]] with [[red bow|red]] and [[white bow]]s [[sleeve bow|on]] its [[long sleeves|sleeves]], a [[black skirt]] also with a [[ribbon-trimmed skirt|ribbon trim]], [[white socks]], and [[black shoes|black]] [[mary janes]]. She is often seen [[holding]] her [[rod of remorse]] or a red [[spider lily]].

title: steven_steel
body:
Steven Steel is a [spoilers] secondary ally [/spoilers] featured in the seventh part of the [[JoJo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[Steel Ball Run]].

Steel is the promoter of the Steel Ball Run race and husband of [[Lucy Steel]]. A [[mature male]] with a colorful life, the Steel Ball Run that he promotes becomes embroiled with him in [[Funny Valentine]]'s schemes.

Steven Steel is a [[mature male]] standing at around 190 cm. He is [[bald]], but covers the top of his head with a smooth cap with serrated edges.

His attire usually consists of a [[high collar]]ed [[long  coat]] decorated with several tassels on the collar and assorted pants. Steven also wears small rectangular glasses.

Namesake Stephen Stills (American musician)

title: variant_reisen
body:
Beastly and psychotic version of [[Reisen Udongein Inaba]] from [[Touhou Igyoukyo]].

Appears as a very large and tall monster [[rabbit girl]] with sharp teeth and fangs, [[glowing eyes|glowing]] [[red eyes]], a skeletal left arm and hand, and a massive multifunctional [[arm cannon]], akin to a Swiss Army knife, on her right arm (almost making her look like a fiddler crab). Instead of a suit and tie, she wears a sort of heavy [[body armor]], although she still wears a [[skirt]]. She appears to be the leader of the rabbit variants.

Like the rest of the moon rabbit variants, she curiously only speaks in broken English (although it is possible that's unintentional and is just a side-effect of a bad machine translation). She also often breaks out into crazed laughter when fighting. [spoiler]Additionally, she appears to be quite interested in rapidly solving [[rubik's cube|Rubik's cubes]] and seems to be quite adept at it.[/spoiler]

title: maritozzo
body:
A cream-filled sweet bun that is a traditional dessert from the Lazio region of Italy, which includes Rome. It has been booming in Japan since around 2020.

Not to be confused with [[cream puff]]. Compared to cream puff, a maritozzo has its cream filling exposed and smoothened, and its buns has a smooth surface. 

h4. External link

* "Fukuoka bakery's maritozzo cream-packed sweet buns taste success in pandemic-hit Japan - The Mainichi":[https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20210521/p2a/00m/0li/042000c]

title: female_dreamseeker_(honkai_impact)
body:
Protagonist for Part 2 of [[Honkai Impact 3rd]]'s main story. Voiced by [[Nakashima Yuki]].

First introduced as a student under the Oxia Data Research Institute, studying the "Sea of Data" and natural calamities in the old city of Langqiu alongside [[Senadina (Deepspace Anchor: First Light)|]]. It is later revealed that she is the avatar of a supercomputer entity created to simulate thousands of iterations of an extinct Mars civilization, primarily for [[Leylah (Honkai Impact)|]] (to whose likeness the Dreamseeker takes) to see if she can uncover the mystery behind [[Senadina (Cocoon of Unwoven)|]]'s disappearance.

Dreamseeker has a [[Male dreamseeker (Honkai Impact)|male form]], however this was revealed by [[Vita (Honkai Impact)|]] to be a bug as the supercomputer was only intended to run one user account - that being [[Leylah (Honkai Impact)|]]'s.

h4. Appearance

* !post #7083824
* !post #7185790
* !post #7189697

title: male_dreamseeker_(honkai_impact)
body:
Protagonist for Part 2 of [[Honkai Impact 3rd]]'s main story for Chapters 1-3.

First introduced as a student under the Oxia Data Research Institute, studying the "Sea of Data" and natural calamities in the old city of Langqiu alongside [[Senadina (Deepspace Anchor: First Light)|]]. It is later revealed that he is a mistakenly created second user account in the Mars supercomputer intended to simulate thousands of iterations of an extinct Mars civilization, as the supercomputer was only intended to run one user account - that being [[Leylah (Honkai Impact)|]]'s, to which the [[Female Dreamseeker (Honkai Impact)|proper user account]] takes after her likeness.

h4. Appearance

title: leylah_(honkai_impact)
body:
Non-playable character in [[Honkai Impact 3rd]]. Voiced by [[Nakashima Yuki]].

The original form of [[Female Dreamseeker (Honkai Impact)|]] and a native to the civilization on Mars. She is one of a few natives who are considered the caretaker gods of the Mars civilization alongside [[Senadina (Cocoon of Unwoven)|]] and [[Nahralab (Honkai Impact)|]]. Following [[Senadina (Cocoon of Unwoven)|]]'s disappearance, she takes on the mantle of the God of Mars; however, in her obsession to find Senadina, she uses a [[Female Dreamseeker (Honkai Impact)|supercomputer]] to simulate their bygone civilization and trace her whereabouts.

h4. Appearance

title: syrian_flag
body:
This tag applies to any national [[flag]]s of [[Syria]] throughout history, such as:

* Flag of Syrian Arab Republic under Baath Party rule (1980-2024), as well as the United Arab Republic: red-white-black horizontal triband with two green [[star (symbol)|stars]] 
* Current flag (2024-present): green-white-black triband with three [[red star]]s. Was also used during the First and Second Republic era (1930-1958), as well as by the Syrian opposition during the [[syrian civil war|civil war]] (2011-2024).

title: bashar_al-assad
body:
Bashar al-Assad (Arabic: بشار الأسد) (born 11 September 1965) was a Syrian [[politician]] who was the 19th president of [[Syria]] from 2000 to 2024 (until his defeat in the Syrian Civil War, after which he fled the country to Russia on December 8th). In addition, he was the commander-in-chief of the [[military|Syrian Armed Forces]] and the secretary-general of the Central Command of the Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party. The son of [[Hafez al-Assad]].

On 8 December 2024, Assad fled Damascus to Russia just before its fall to the rebels, ending 54 years of the Assad family's rule.

h4. See also
* [[Syrian Civil War]]
* [[Tag Group:People]]

h4. External links
* Wikipedia: "Bashar al-Assad":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bashar_al-Assad

title: uchi_no_hime-sama_ga_ichiban_kawaii
body:
Uchi no Hime-sama ga Ichiban Kawaii (My Princess Is The Cutest) was a Japanese Card-based RPG for iOS that ran from 2013 (iOS)/2014 (Android) to 2022.

In Uchihime, the princesses of the land had been imprisoned into crystals by the Demon King. The player takes the role of a prince who was cursed into an [[kaeru_ouji|anthropomorphic frog]]. However, despite being cursed with a seemingly permanent and debilitating transmogrification, the prince can still battle the army of the Demon King. Together with the help of [[anna (uchihime)|Anna]], a fairy who acts as a magical slingshot and a guide, the prince sets course to rescue the captured princesses and defeat the Demon King.

The main storyline revolves around four princesses: [[lina_princella|Princess Lina]], [[akane_garnet|Princess Akane]], [[sapphire emerald|Princess Sapphire]], and [[clarice_lapis|Princess Lapis]].


h4.See Also

title: kusakabe_mei
body:
Mei Kusakabe (草壁 メイ, Kusakabe Mei) is the four-year-old protagonist and the little sister of Satsuki in [i][[Tonari No Totoro|My Neighbor Totoro]][/i] and [i]Mei and the Kittenbus[/i]. She is the daughter of Tatsuo and Yasuko Kusakabe.

She is also one of the mascots of the [[Ghibli]] Museum in Mitaka.

title: kusakabe_satsuki
body:
Kusakabe Satsuki is one of the two main protagonists (alongside her sister [[Kusakabe Mei]]) in the 1988 animated [[Studio Ghibli]] film [i][[Tonari no totoro|My Neighbor Totoro]][/i].

She was voiced by Noriko Hidaka in the original Japanese version, Dakota Fanning in the [[Disney]] dub and the late Lisa Michelson in the Streamline dub.

title: mechabare
body:
Exposed mechanical, robotic, or cybernetic body parts, systems, innards, etc of a [[cyborg]], [[android]], or other robotic character.

Use this tag for:

* Exposed parts or inner workings of a [[cyborg]], [[android]], or robotic character.
* Diagrams, schematics, x-ray views, or other inner views of a robotic character's parts or inner workings.
* [[Damaged]], missing, or obviously artificial limbs or body parts.

body:
[i]Thorns, Guard Operator of Rhodes Island, wastes not an ounce of energy, calculating each strike meticulously.[/i]

h4. Profile

Born in the Iberian hinterland, Thorns left his hometown in the midst of local religious strife. After leaving, he was invited to join Rhodes Island. 

Knowledgeable in pharmacology and frequently experiments with various poisons and toxins, and is also exceptionally skilled in the Iberian swordsmanship technique known as [i]Destreza[/i]. His fencing teacher was [[Aulus (arknights)|]].

Easily misunderstood due to his blunt and uncaring demeanor, shrewd, and extremely forgetful regarding his appearance.

His motif is based on the black long-spined [[sea urchin]].

His [[voice actor]]s are [[Ishikawa Kaito]] (Japanese), Xu Xiang (Chinese), and Hong Bum-ki (Korean). His art designer is [[Huanxiang Heitu]].

title: shaded_face
body:
When the upper face or eyes are shadowed without a tangible light source.

Often used to convey a wide variety of strong emotions, such as [[angry|anger]], [[disgust]], [[desperation]], [[surprised|shock]], intense [[crying]] or sinister intentions, or to obscure the character's appearance for a [[faceless|mysterious effect]]. Can be used for comedic effect.

If only one side of the face is shaded, use [[partially shaded face]].

Do not use this tag when the character's face is shadowed simply because of a light source - use [[shade]] instead.

title: birdo
body:
[[Mario_(series)|]] character first appearing in [i][[Yume Koujou: Doki Doki Panic]][/i], then later incorporated into the Mario franchise proper with the international version of [i][[Super Mario Bros. 2]][/i]. Birdos were a reoccurring mid-boss and subordinate of [[Wart_(mario)|]] during the attempted conquest of Subcon. Since then however the species has become overall less antagonistic and much more friendlier. 

They are [[reptile_girl|dinosaur-like]] with large snouts in place of a mouth, from which they shoot white [[egg]]s out of to attack. They have long [[eyelashes]], [[eyeshadow]] and wear an [[ornate ring]]. They wear an [[huge_bow|oversized bow]] on the back of their heads as well as have [[claws]].

Birdos come in a variety of colors, though the main color is pink. Compared to [[Toad_(mario)|]]s and [[Yoshi]]s, Birdos are much more consistently represented by a singular individual in a given game, where it's much rarer to see the rest of the species or a multitude in one place.
