title: lena_luthor
body:
[b]Lena Luthor[/b] is the name given to two characters in [[DC comics]], the first Lena is [[Lex Luthor]]'s younger sister while the second Lena is Lex's daughter who was named after her aunt. Both Lena's in the comics are the few people Lex cares about yet both his sister and daughter have a distant relationship with him due to his status as a supervillain.

The first Lena Luthor was portrayed by Katie McGrath in [[Supergirl (2015)|CW's Supergirl]]. In the show, Lena befriends Kara Danvers/[[Supergirl]], unaware of the latter's true identity while trying to redeem her family's name due to her brother's villainous actions.

title: dr._arach
body:
Character from [[Tsukihime (Remake)]], first appearing in [i]Tsukihime -A piece of blue glass moon-[/i], and is mentioned in [[Melty Blood: Type Lumina]]. She serves as the Tohno family doctor.

An energetic scientist with a habit of skipping work.[b]Neiko Arach[/b], nicknamed [b]Dr. Arach[/b], attended university with [[tohno Makihisa]] and studied architecture alongside him. It was through this connection that she became the family’s resident doctor following Makihisa’s death.

Everything Dr. Arach does appears to be done on a whim, and she refers to to herself as a "free spirit pulled away from her roots".

Arach is a woman with light [[brown hair]] and [[amber eyes]]. She doesn’t wear makeup, and her hair is arranged in a very messy way. She wears a white [[lab coat]] with a yellow-and-black checkerboard pattern on the inside over an [[orange blouse]], [[black skirt]], black-and-orange [[tights]], and black [[high heels]]. She has very [[large breasts]], and wears her blouse with the top opened as to completely expose her [[bra and cleavage]]. Around her neck is a gold [[necklace]] with a [[red jewel]] attached to it.


h4. Appearance

body:
A character introduced in the [[Tsukihime (remake)|Tsukihime remake]]. She is an executor of the church like [[Ciel (tsukihime)|]] posing as a teacher at the high school, and is featured prominently in Ciel's route.

Noel appears one day as [[Tohno Shiki]] 's homeroom teacher and both the English and PE teacher after his previous one died suddenly, going by the name [b]Noel Aizome (愛染ノエル, Aizome Noeru?)[/b]

Noel is a woman with [[brunette hair]], [[brown eyes]], and a mature look about her. She keeps her hair in a [[side ponytail]] with a pink elastic tie. When undercover as a teacher, she wears a [[blue blazer]] and [[pencil skirt]] over a [[white dress shirt]], [[black tights]], and [[high heels]]. 

When working as an Executor, she wears a button-up nun’s [[habit]] with a cutout that exposes her legs and  knee-high combat boots. Occasionally, she also wears the traditional [[coif]] and [[veil]] of a nun with this outfit.

title: oh_that's_real_nice_(meme)
body: Oh That's Real Nice, also known as SpongeBob Fish Looking Into Toilet or Martin Looking Into A Toilet, refers to an exploitable meme template taken from an episode of [[SpongeBob SquarePants (Series)|]] in which the fish character Martin looks into a toilet and sees SpongeBob's hyper-realistic body floating in the water. Martin's quote "Oh, that's real nice," was later used as the caption for the screencap and thus became a reaction image. Then, meme creators recaptioned the meme, replacing the words "real nice" with other objects, people or concepts imagined to be in the toilet and found by Martin. The most common phrases inserted into the phrasal template related to shock media not intended to be seen. The template trended across Reddit, iFunny and Instagram, among other platforms, predominantly in the early 2020s.

Mentally ill Japanese users being who they are sent her negative comments. She attempted suicide but it failed and the negative comments stopped, and this incident has been largely buried since then.

Since mentioning in the voice drama that she uploaded utattemita videos as 銭麻 (Zenima), she became known for ガッツリ宣伝 ([[holding sign|adamant ad-pushing]]). title: hollow_knight_(character)
body:
The titular character of [[Hollow Knight]]. It has [[horns]], wears a [[grey cloak|grey]] [[cloak]], and wields a [[nail (hollow knight)| nail]].

[spoiler]Contrary to many first-time players' expectations, it is [i]not[/i] the [[knight_(hollow_knight)|player character]]. Unlike the Knight, it has a [[crack]] in its skull, has only [[missing limb|one arm]], and is sometimes depicted with [[solid eyes|solid]] [[orange eyes]].[/spoiler]

The [[aged down|young]] form of this character uses this tag, as[spoilers] the [[Pure Vessel]] tag is only used for the form of the character seen during the Pure Vessel boss fight.[/spoilers]

[spoilers]The final and penultimate boss for different endings, [b]The Hollow Knight[/b] is a child of the [[Pale King (Hollow Knight)|Pale King]] and the [[White Lady (Hollow Knight)|White Lady]], born and trained to be a vessel for the [[Radiance (Hollow Knight)|Radiance]]. It was once the [[Pure Vessel]] before being corrupted by the Radiance.[/spoilers]

body:

body:

title: pepper_(spice)
body:
A spice made out of [[peppercorn]] drupes that are dried. The peppercorns may be sold whole so that they could be hand-milled by consumers in a [[pepper mill]], or pre-milled so it can be dispensed in a [[pepper shaker]]. While black pepper is the most common color, other varieties exist such as white pepper, green pepper, and even pink pepper. More often than not, ground pepper causes people to sneeze because the piperine in pepper irritates the nose.

h4.See also

* [[salt]]
** [[salt shaker]]
* [[Tag Group:Food Tags]]

title: analog_clock
body:
A type of [[clock]] normally consisting of a circular [[dial]] with twelve numbers, one for each hour in an AM/PM system, a short hand indicating the hour, and a long hand indicating the minute. Minutes are grouped into batches of 5, though sometimes there may be smaller lines between the hour markers for each minute interval. May or may not contain an additional hand indicating the seconds.

Certain unique types of analog clocks may have greater or fewer than twelve hours, though twelve is the most common.

title: karna_(fate)
body:
Lancer-class Servant in [[Fate/Apocrypha]] (Lancer of Red) and a Servant of [[Jinako Carigiri]] in [[Fate/extra CCC]], where he is referred to as Launcher.

Depicted as a [[white hair]]ed man with [[blue eyes]], he dons a unique set of [[armor]] with a [[cape]]. In Fate/Extra CCC, his cape is replaced with a [[fur collar]] and metal scales.

title: grace_note
body:
In musical notation, a grace note is distinguished from a regular note by print size. A grace note is indicated by printing a note that is much smaller than a regular note, sometimes with a slash through the note stem (if two or more grace notes, there might be a slash through the note stem of the first note but not the subsequent grace note).

You can see an example at the very upper right corner of the sheet music in post #2863696.

title: fermata
body:
A [[musical note]] indicating that the note should be prolonged beyond its normal duration or note value would indicate. Exactly how much longer it is held is up to the discretion of the performer or conductor, but twice as long is common. A fermata looks like a bracket turned 90 degrees with a circle placed inside it, "like this":https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e7/Fermata_round.png.

title: devils_tower
body: [b]Devils Tower[/b] is a prominent laccolithic [[butte]] in the Black Hills of northeastern Wyoming, USA.  It stands 867 feet above ground level with its summit at an altitude of 5,112 above mean sea level.  Devils Tower is the main feature of the eponymous Devils Tower National Monument.  It was made famous in popular culture by its appearance in Steven Spielberg's 1977 motion picture [i][[Close Encounters of the Third Kind]][/i].  In common with other geographic features of the American West which received their English names in the 19th century (e.g., Pikes Peak in Colorado), its name is possessive but officially lacks the apostrophe that would be required by modern English grammar.

title: dunkirk_(movie)
body:
[b]Dunkirk[/b] is a 2017 historical [[war]] film written, directed and produced by Christopher Nolan that depicts the [[Dunkirk Evacuation]] of [[World War II]] from the perspectives of the land, sea and air. 

It was produced by Nolan and Emma Thomas. Its ensemble cast includes Fionn Whitehead, Tom Glynn-Carney, Jack Lowden, Harry Styles in his film debut, Aneurin Barnard, James D'Arcy, Barry Keoghan, Kenneth Branagh, [[Cillian Murphy]], Mark Rylance and [[Tom Hardy]].

title: tom_hardy
body: Edward Thomas Hardy (born 15 September 1977) is an English actor. After studying acting at the Drama Centre London he made his film debut in Ridley Scott's Black Hawk Down in 2001. He had supporting roles in the films [[Star Trek]]: Nemesis (2002) and RocknRolla (2008), and went on to star in Bronson (2008), Warrior (2011), Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy (2011), Lawless (2012), This Means War (2012) and Locke (2013). In 2015 he starred as "Mad" Max Rockatansky in [[Mad Max: Fury Road]] and both Kray twins in Legend, and was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor for his role in The Revenant. Hardy appeared in three Christopher Nolan films: [[Inception]] (2010), [[The Dark Knight Rises]] (2012) and [[Dunkirk_(movie)|dunkirk]] (2017). He has since starred as the title character in the film [[Venom]] (2018) and its two sequels (2021 and 2024).

title: inception
body:
<quote>We can go deeper...</quote>

A 2010 critically and commercially acclaimed American/British science fiction action film starring [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] as [[Dominic Cobb]], a professional thief who steals information by infiltrating the subconscious of his targets. DiCaprio is accompanied by an ensemble cast including Ken Watanabe, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Marion Cotillard, Elliot Page, [[Tom Hardy]], Dileep Rao, Cillian Murphy, Tom Berenger, and Michael Caine. The film won four Academy Awards for Best Cinematography, Best Sound Editing, Best Sound Mixing, and Best Visual Effects.

title: the_dark_knight_rises
body:
The Dark Knight Rises is a [[2012]] superhero film directed by Christopher Nolan, who co-wrote the screenplay with his brother Jonathan Nolan, and the story with David S. Goyer. Based on the [[DC Comics]] character [[Batman]], it is the final installment in Nolan's The Dark Knight trilogy, and the sequel to [[The Dark Knight]] (2008). The film stars [[Christian Bale]] as [[Bruce Wayne]] / Batman, alongside Anne Hathaway, Gary Oldman, [[Tom Hardy]], [[Morgan Freeman]], Marion Cotillard, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, and Michael Caine. Eight years after the events of The Dark Knight, the terrorist [[Bane]] forces Bruce Wayne to resume his role as Batman and save Gotham City from nuclear destruction.

title: bright_noa
body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]Bright Noa[/b] was first introduced in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] (1979). He is a skilled [[Earth Federation]]/[[AEUG]]/[[earth federation space forces|Londo Bell]] captain who commands many [[space]] battleships, notably the [[White Base]] and the [[Argama]]. A meme ([[Bright Slap]]) sprung up from the way he literally [[slapping|slaps]] some sense into his subordinates, notably [[Amuro Ray]].

Has appeared in many U.C. series and anime like [[Zeta Gundam]] (1985), [[Gundam ZZ]] (1986), [[Char's Counterattack]] (1988) and [[Gundam Unicorn]] (2010).

Father of [[Hathaway Noa]] and [[Cheimin Noa]]. [spoilers]Husband of [[Mirai Yashima]][/spoilers]

Voiced by [[Suzuoki Hirotaka]].

title: phoenix_ikki
body:
One of the main five Bronze Saints in [[Saint Seiya]].
Like the other four Bronze Saints, he along with 99 other orphans was kidnapped as a child by the Graad Foundation and sent across the world in order to undergo hellish training for seven years and return as a Saint.

In Ikki's case, he was sent to one of the most dangerous training sites of all, Death Queen Island. His time on the island drove him insane and when he returned as the Phoenix Saint, he wanted nothing more than destroy the Graad Foundation and its surviving Saints. 

Following their fight within the inner recesses of Mount Fuji, he exhibits a change of heart upon being defeated by [[pegasus_seiya|Seiya]] shortly before dying in the ensuing cave-in.
 
[Spoiler]It's later revealed he survived due to the Phoenix Saint's resurrective properties. From then on, he becomes an occasional ally of [[Athena (saint seiya)|]] and her Saints.[/Spoiler]

He is protective of his younger brother, [[andromeda_shun|Shun]].

Initially voiced by Hideyuki Hori from 1986-2004 in Japan, then [[konishi_katsuyuki|Katsuyuki Konishi]] from 2005 till date.

title: platypus
body:
A platypus, also known as the duck-billed platypus, is a semi-aquatic [[animal]] native to [[Australia]].  They're carnivores that feed on a diet of insects and small crustaceans.  Platypuses are one of the few mammals that lay eggs.  They're also one of the few mammals that possess venom, with males possessing a spike on their hindleg that can deliver venom.  Their venom is described as excruciatingly painful to humans, but it is not lethal.

h4. See also

title: date_a_live
body:
A light novel series written by Tachibana Koushi and illustrated by [[Tsunako]].

In the future, spherical so-called "space quakes" have destroyed a great part of Earth's landmass. In response militaries and scientific communities all over the world have worked together to find out the origin of the occurrences, to little effect.

Enter [[Itsuka Shido]], a young man of above average skill in school but no experience with girls. By accident he stays near the area that was just ravaged by a space quake, only to find [[yatogami tohka|a girl in a warrior dress]] who threatens to kill him. Before he can say much, she disappears. Afterward he learns that she, among others, is a spirit. Spirits come from another world and cause destruction whenever they enter the human world. Shidou is now given a choice to see how the military kills spirits, or take another option: date the spirits, make them fall in love with and surrender their powers to him so they can live among humans without fear of being hunted.

A very dating sim-like adventure begins for Shidou.

title: tokisaki_kurumi
body:
A character from [[Date A Live]]. She is voiced by [[Sanada Asami]].

Kurumi is one of the spirits appearing in our world from another realm. Unlike most spirits who are shy and/or bashful, she is openly easy going and very pro-active towards sex. However, she is also vicious and brutal. Her powers revolve around time and control of shadows, with which she can absorb her enemies.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] and possesses [[heterochromia]], with one [[red eyes|red eye]] and one [[yellow eyes|yellow]] [[clock eyes|clock eye]].

She wears a [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[red dress|red]]/[[orange dress|orange]] [[lolita fashion|lolita dress]], along with a [[lolita hairband]], [[frilled choker|frilled]] [[black choker]], [[detached sleeves]], [[red ribbon]]s, [[thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]]. She also has [[uneven twintails]] and wields two [[flintlock]] pistols of differing length.

When not in her Astral Dress, she can be seen with [[low twintails]] and [[hair over one eye|hair covering her left eye]]. She also wears the [[Raizen High School uniform]] when attending said school.

h4. Official art

* !post #2676029: Profile

title: gal_farion
body:
Gal Farion (ガル・ファリオン) is the current Sword God of the Sword God Style, living in the Holy Land of Swords. Ranked sixth among the Seven Great Powers, he's so powerful that even Water God [[Reida Reia]] doubts she could block his blade. He's the father of [[Nina Farion]] and trained [[Ghislaine Dedoldia]], gifting her the sword Hiramune when she became a Sword King.

Gal shares [[Eris Greyrat]]’s dream of defeating the Dragon God [[Orsted (Mushoku Tensei)]]. Impressed by her resolve, he agrees to train her and arranges for her to learn from all three sword styles.

title: broly_(dragon_ball_z)
body:
Originally an anime-only character designed by [[Toriyama Akira]], serving as the main antagonist of [[Dragon Ball Z]] Movie 8, [i]Broly: Legendary Super Saiyan[/i], and Movie 10, [i]Broly: Second Coming[/i], with a variation of the character, [[Bio Broly]], serving as the antagonist of Movie 11, [i]Bio-Broly.[/i] He is the son of [[Paragus (dragon ball z)|]].

His most identifying visual elements include:
* pre-transformation: the [[circlet]] and [[armlet]]s, golden, with the former having a blue [[forehead jewel]]; medium-to-long black or brown hair
* constant: [[gold earrings|golden]] [[hoop earrings]], golden [[bracer]]s/[[vambraces]], and the [[gold necklace|golden]] [[necklace]], the latter two having a blue gem embedded in it; [[white pants]] paired with a red robbed material, [[gold boots|golden]] [[boots]], [[topless male]] and a [[monkey tail]]; scars on [[scar on chest|chest]] and [[scar on stomach|stomach]] (only if based on DBZ Movie 10).
* post-transformation: incredibly [[muscular]] body, [[spiked hair|spiked]] blonde or green hair, based on scene ([[Legendary Super Saiyan]]), [[no pupils]]

Finally appeared in canon form with the release of Movie 20, [i][[Dragon Ball Super Broly]][/i] in late 2018, [[Broly (Dragon Ball Super)|redone]] under Toriyama's supervision.

Due to the memetic status of DBZ Movie 8, it is common for artists to redraw scenes or screencaps from the movie with other characters, with the character replacing Broly being [[manlification|manlified]] into looking like Broly himself.

h4. See also

* [[Broly culo (meme)]]

title: yuudachi_(azur_lane)
body:
Personification of the fourth ship of the [i]Shiratsuyu[/i]-class destroyers, [i]Yuudachi[/i] (夕立), in [[Azur Lane]].

Introducing herself as the "Mad Dog of Solomon", her personality takes the dog-like mannerisms that fans gave her [[yuudachi (kancolle)|Kantai Collection counterpart]] and dials them up even further. Yuudachi is highly aggressive, often growling and even outright howling. Like many dogs, she is also food-motivated, and often cannot stop thinking about the consumption of freshly-cooked meat.

Character design by [[Saru]], voiced by [[Takamori Natsumi]].

Yuudachi has [[long hair|long]] [[silver hair]] tied into at least one [[side ponytail]] on her right and a [[braid]] from her left sidelock. She has [[red eyes]], [[wolf ears]] with metal plates over the outside, and a [[wolf tail]]. Like Shigure, her outfit consists of a modified [[serafuku]], with a white [[crop top]], [[puffy short sleeves]], a [[black sailor collar]], and a [[red ribbon]]. Below the waist, she wears a [[black skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]], [[white socks|white]] [[loose socks]] and [[red footwear|red]] [[rudder footwear|rudder]] [[high heels]]. Additionally, she has [[fingerless gloves]] with red and white leather [[cuffs]], [[stuffed wolf]] toy near her hip, and a rose [[tattoo]] on her right hip.

Her [[rigging]] has a single twin [[ship turret|turret]] on her right, a quad [[torpedo tubes|torpedo tube]] on her right, and a [[smokestack]] on her back. These are all in solid black and white paint-scheme.

title: jerrick_(mountainsmithy)
body:
bio time:
    Near the beginning of history, Jerrick was given eternal youth. With this gift, Jerrick became an exorcists and demon hunter; instead of just removing demons from the possessed, Jerrick physically punches them out and kills them. Jerrick fights unarmed with vicious brutality and a sharp, analytical mind. Jerrick has strengthen and honed his body, building his muscles into armor. His speed and reflexes are enough to dodge bullets shot from point blank. Jerrick’s wild, beast-of-a-man temperament has also granted him an animal-like sixth sense for danger. Jerrick has enough stamina to fight continuously for several days before passing out. In addition to his already nearly superhuman physical abilities, Jerrick gets even stronger, faster, tougher, more durable the more intense and berserk he gets.
    Jerrick is incredibly hot-blooded and is swift to kill demons and monsters. He is still a man of morals and convictions and is quite reserved when it comes to killing humans and will do so only when necessary. When not fighting, Jerrick manages to be reasonably calm. He always tries to bring out the best in the people around him, although he usually does that by teasing and sometimes outright insulting them about their faults. It works but he often comes across as rude as a result.

title: pheasant-tailed_jacana
body:
Latin: [i]Hydrophasianus chirurgus[/i]
JP: レンカク

Unmistakable, with large feet evolved for wading on lily pads and breeding plumage marked by the elongated black central tail feathers, white front, wing, and silky golden nape.  Body is chocolate brown, with a white face; the back of the crown is black with white stripes running down the sides of the neck that separate the white of the front of neck and the golden yellow of the nape. 

The wings are predominantly white; in flight the white wing shows a black border formed by black on the outermost primaries and the tips of the outer secondaries and the primaries. The wing coverts are pale brown and the scapulars may be glossed green or purple. 

Found in tropical Asia from Yemen to the Philippines. Females are larger than the males and are polyandrous, laying several clutches that are raised by different males in their harem.

body: A family of [[bird]]s, all around the size of a chicken. Historically were raised for meat, but now are mostly pets.

title: kiwi_(bird)
body:
Latin: [i]Apteryx sp.[/i]

A small, flightless bird native to New Zealand. They have shaggy brown, hairlike feathers, long slim beaks with nostrils at the end for smelling prey, and are about the size of a chicken. There are five known species.

Kiwi are the smallest ratites (the group containing [[ostrich]], [[emu]] & [[cassowary]]).

For the fruit, see [[kiwi (fruit)]].

h4. See also
* [[Tag Group:Birds]]

title: nightingale_(bird)
body:
Latin: [i]Luscinia megarhynchos[/i]
JP: サヨナキドリ [i]sayonakidori[/i]

The "Common Nightingale":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_nightingale] is a drab European bird renowned for its song. It frequently sings at night, a behavior from which its name is derived.

The nightingale is plain brown above, buff to white below and has a reddish tail. Eastern populations have paler upperparts and a stronger face-pattern including a white eyebrow.

The range of the Common Nightingale does not extend past south-east Asia, and is [b]not[/b] frequently depicted in Japanese art. Instead:

h4. That Bird Might Also be...
* [[Japanese bush warbler]]: has also been known as the Japanese nightingale due to its song.  It is similarly drab in appearance.
* [[Japanese white-eye]]: has also been confused with a nightingale, but is distinct in appearance, having green plumage.
* "Red-billed leiothrix":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red-billed_leiothrix]: also known as the Japanese nightingale, but not native to Japan, making this common name a misnomer.
h4. See also
* "eBird - Common Nightingale":[https://ebird.org/species/comnig1]
* [[Japanese bush warbler]]
* [[Japanese white-eye]]
* [[Tag Group:Birds]]

title: moa_(animal)
body:
Latin: [i]Dinornithiformes[/i] Order

The [[extinct]] moa was a type of flightless bird endemic to New Zealand. There were 9 species, the largest of which reached about 12' in height and weighed about 510lb. 

Moa were hunted to extinction in about 1300-1440 by the Māori. The primary non-human predator of the moa was [[Haast's eagle]].

title: dove
body:
For tagging purposes, this tag refers to the white or mostly white birds, such as the "dove of peace" that is commonly associated with the term "dove." 

The term dove is frequently used interchangeably with the term pigeon.  When used more specifically, the term refers to smaller members of the bird family Columbidae, whose members are referred to by either the terms dove or pigeon. Members of this family fall under two major groups based on their diet, with one group predominately eating seeds and the other predominately eating fruits.

Gray or bluish-gray birds should be tagged [[pigeon]] instead.

[[common emerald dove]]

body:

The exact way of carrying can vary from having straight legs, to slightly sitting on the other's arm, to a [[leg lock]]. If the person being carried is significantly sitting and hugging the other from the side, it's [[child carry]] instead.

title: racetrack

A purpose-built course for [[car]] or [[motorcycle]] racing, usually with seating for fans to watch. For racetracks built specifically for [[horse racing]]]], see [[horse racing track]]. For the type of track used for track and field events, see [[running track]].

Motorsport tracks are typically paved, though dirt tracks for rallycross, motocross, and certain stock cars are also used. Horse racing tracks are always dirt-based, with some tracks (such as those in Europe and Japan) also having grass surfaces.

title: third_wheel
body:
When two people act ”intimate” close to someone clearly trying to focus on something else (such as sleeping, studying, reading, etc.), usually (but not necessarily) prompting the person trying to focus to feel embarrassment, [[unamused]], or arousal.

Intimate activities may be romantic (Ex: [[flirting]]) or sexual in nature.

If the intimate activities are sexual, then the sexual activities should not be happening to the person when he/she is trying to focus nor should they be happening [[public indecency|in public]]. Such activities should be done in the safety of the performers' own private space.

The person trying to focus should not be intentionally focusing on witnessing/listening to the intimate acts such as in [[voyeurism]] or [[eavesdropping]].

title: mithrun
body:
One of the "Canaries" in [[Dungeon Meshi]], a squad of [[elf|elven]] criminals and nobles sent to dungeons to evaluate the danger they pose to the world. He's easily recognized by his [[lazy_eye|false eye]] (sometimes covered by his messy [[silver_hair|silver]] bangs), [[notched_ear|cut-off eartips]], and [[expressionless]] face.

Mithrun was at one point the "master" of a dungeon, and as such has unique insight into how they work. [spoilers]His tenure came to an end when [[goat (dungeon meshi)|the demon controlling the dungeon]] ate all of his desires except for his newfound desire to kill demons. As such, the rest of the squad has to remind him to do things like eat, drink, and sleep, because he has no desire to do them on his own.[/spoilers] He is an expert teleporter, who can even attack by teleporting his opponents inside of brick walls, although this ability is hindered somewhat by his lack of depth perception and directional awareness.

His squadmates include:
* [[Pattadol]] (second-in-command)
* [[Cithis]] (his "babysitter")
* [[Fleki]]
* [[Otta (dungeon meshi)|]]
* [[Lycion]]

h4. External links
* "Adventurer's Bible entry":[https://mangadex.org/chapter/6665b0ad-97e2-4f88-8249-0148a4c6e123]

title: cats_are_scared_of_cucumbers
body: [[Cat]]s or cat-related characters acting [[scared]], [[surprised|shocked]], [[nervous]], cautious, etc. towards the sudden presence of a [[cucumber]]. Often result in [[jumping]], [[puffing up]], [[wide-eyed]], [[screaming]], freezing, backing off, etc.  In reality, they are actually spooked by something appearing behind them when it was previously not there, so other objects other than cucumbers can also spook them if done the same way.

title: colorpoint
body:
A form of heat-sensitive [[albino|albinism]] in animals, most well-known for giving [[siamese cat]]s their unique appearance. It can appear in any type of [[cat]], and in other animals such as [[rabbit]]s as well.

Colorpoint causes a light overall coat with pigmentation gathering at the extremities.

* "Wikipedia: Points (coat color)":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Points_(coat_color)

title: sphinx
body:
In [[Ancient Egyptian]] culture, a sphinx is a creature that has the body of a [[lion]], while the head could be a human, [[sheep|ram]], or [[bird]]. They are most commonly assigned to protect the sacred places.

In [[Greek mythology]], a sphinx is a monster with a female human torso and a lion body. The sphinx in Greek mythology is usually seen preying on adventurers by asking riddles to decide their fate.

Not to be confused with a [[sphynx cat]].

title: morning_rescue
body:
Japanese soft drink apparently made from turmeric"[1]":[/wiki_pages/25611#dtext-external-links]. It became famous among anime fans worldwide because its commercial"[2]":[/wiki_pages/25611#dtext-external-links] aired during the original broadcasts of [[mahou_shoujo_madoka_magica|Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica]]'s episode 2 through 4 and was also left in gg's fansub releases. (gg even added the commercial back into episode 5 even though it didn't air). The apparent hilarity of the commercial, and the fact that it drastically contrasted with Madoka's overall atmosphere, contributed to its popularity among fans. Morning Rescue stopped being manufactured in 2011 because of supply chain disruptions caused by the [[2011 tohoku earthquake and tsunami|Tohoku Earthquake]]. 

[b]Note[/b]: Do not make this a "copyright" tag, as it is an object/meme, not a series.

h4#external-links.External links

[1] http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turmeric
[2] http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PD-_oLjmCGY

title: geara_zulu
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Gundam Unicorn]].

[b]AMS-129 Geara Zulu[/b]

The successor to the [[Geara Doga]] [[mobile suit|MS]] - cheap, reliable and easy to produce and pilot, in line with its distant ancestor, the [[Zaku II]]. Its head has been redesigned and resembles a [i][[Stahlhelm]][/i] with a gas mask shaped vent, and its improved [[beam_rifle|beam machine gun]] seems heavily inspired by the [[StG 44]]. 

While not cutting edge by any stretch of the imagination, it's still a serviceable, solid MS for [[Full Frontal]]'s Sleeves - his personal brand of [[Neo Zeon]].

h4. Related development
* [[Zee Zulu]]

title: zee_zulu
body:
A fictional manned giant combat robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Gundam Unicorn]].

[b]AMS-129M Zee Zulu[/b]

An amphibious version of the [[Geara Zulu]] [[mobile_suit|MS]] developed by [[neo_zeon|The Sleeves]] for use by the Zeon Remnants left on Earth. The new units, aside from the modifications for amphibious operation, possessed a set of extendable Heat Claws on each arm and wielded a powerful beam machine gun equipped with a grenade launcher. 

However, despite being much more advanced than the decades-old models operated by the Remnants, even the Zee Zulu was nowhere near a match for the [[Byalant Custom]], which effortlessly destroyed the two units during the Battle of Torrington.

title: the_o_ii
body:
A fictional manned combat robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]PMX-003 The-O II[/b]

The [b]PMX-003 The-O II[/b], later renamed [b]"Hauer"[/b] or semi-recursively the [b]"Neo-Geo"[/b], was a heavy land-combat [[mobile suit|MS]] developed by [[Neo Zeon]] engineers based upon some acquired knowledge from working alongside [[Paptimus Scirocco]]. 

Reenvisioning the original The-O as a possible heavy siege mobile suit, the The-O II is equipped well for this task, possessing heavy armor, a pair of [[beam cannon]]s in the chest, a rear missile launcher, twin machine cannons in it's neck area, and two sub-arms wielding beam sabers in it's front skirt. Along with all this a powerful 120mm machine gun, with greater firepower than equivalent weapons of previous conflicts.

However, an earlier version previously appeared in [i][[Azur Lane: Slow Ahead|Slow Ahead]][/i] (sometimes with white [[high heels]] instead of black, with the tips of the leotard down or with a jacket over it), including the anime, which led to fans clamoring for it to be included in the game (this is not to be confused with that version).

title: alice_(genshin_impact)
body:
A character from [[Genshin Impact]]. Also known as "A", she is a powerful [[witch|sorceress]] who is the founder of the Hexenzirkel and a famous adventurer who wrote the "Teyvat Travel Guide". She is the mother of [[Klee (genshin impact)|]] and created [[Dodoco (genshin impact)|]] as a friend for Klee. 

She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[blonde hair]], [[red eyes]] and [[pointy ears]]. 

Voiced by Rachel Kimsey in English, [[Inoue Kikuko]] in Japanese and Zhang Qi in Chinese.

h4. Appearance

* !post #9671453: Default
* !post #9424869: [[Alice (Prelude to Moonlight) (genshin impact)|Prelude to Moonlight]]

h4. See also

* [[List of Genshin Impact characters]]

h4. External links

* "Genshin Impact Wiki: Alice":https://genshin-impact.fandom.com/wiki/Alice

title: greyscale_with_colored_background
body:
A common composition where a [[greyscale]] subject is on a colored background, usually also a [[simple background]].

Do not tag these as [[greyscale]], [[partially colored]] or [[spot color]].

If small parts of the subject, not part of the background, are colored, such as the subject's eyes, [[spot color]] can be used. If the subject has enough coloring that you'd tag it [[partially colored]], use [[partially colored]] instead and do not use this tag.

h4. Examples

* !post #5782342
* !post #5576860: spot color
* !post #9655235

h4. See also

* [[monochrome background]]

title: head_wings
body:
[[Wings]] that are attached to the head. A common feature on the [[demon girl]], but other creatures may have them, such as [[bird_girl|bird girls]]. If a character's hair is actually wing-shaped, use [[hair wings]]. If the wings are attached to a character's headgear rather than being part of the character's body, use [[winged helmet]] or [[winged hat]].

Not to be confused with [[feather hair]] or [[hair wings]].

title: flag
body:
A flag is a piece of fabric, often flown from a pole or mast. Often decorated with emblems, symbols, or shapes to represent one's country or an event. Soldiers may be carrying a [[war flag]].

[[Flag]] is only applicable if the fabric in question is horizontally-oriented, if it flows vertically use [[banner]] instead.

title: itano_circus
body:
An attack where a ridiculously large number of [[missile]]s are launched from one fighter [[jet]] or [[robot]] at a target or targets, regardless of tactical necessity. It's often characterized by the twisting, turning and crisscrossing [[missile trail]]s, emphasized by the missiles or beam weapons firing along trajectories that are at an unlikely angle off of their target before making sudden turns in order to hit it (an effect that's been dubbed [b]Roboteching[/b] in the West).

Named after anime artist, animation director, and producer Itano Ichirou, and primarily comes from the anime franchise [[MACROSS]] and its [[choujikuu yousai macross|first series]] released in the early [[1980s (style)|80s]], with its origin series lending the additional name [b]Macross Missile Massacre[/b]. The sub-effect of 'roboteching' is named after MACROSS' westernized equivalent in [[ROBOTECH]].

body:
A fictional [[military]] [[spacecraft]] from the [[Gundam]] franchise. It first appeared in the [[Char's Counterattack]] anime film from 1988. Also appears in [[Gundam Unicorn]] (2010).

It is the flagship of the [[Earth Federation Space Forces]] [b]Londo Bell Fleet[/b] under the command of [[Bright Noa]].

title: hastur_(nyaruko-san)
body:
[b]"The Deity of Wind"[/b]

A character from [[Haiyore! Nyaruko-san]]. A being of Hastur, he has the ability to control [[wind]]. He initially came to earth due to some business with his father's organization, but later stayed due to orders to protect [[Yasaka Mahiro]]. He likes Mahiro (disregarding his own [[trap|gender]]), and makes certain advances to catch his attention, albeit the feeling is not mutual. As a being of Hastur, he disguises himself with the form of a small boy with [[blonde hair]], [[blue eyes]], a [[braid]], and [[antenna hair]]. He always wears yellow clothes as a reference to Hastur's origin in [[The King in Yellow]].

title: hector_(fire_emblem)
body:
[[lilina (fire emblem)|Lilina]]'s father, and one of the main protagonists of [[Fire Emblem: the Blazing Blade]].  He is the younger brother of Marquess Ostia, [[uther (fire emblem)|Uther]], during the events of Blazing Blade. He is the Marquess himself by [[Fire Emblem: the Binding Blade]], where he dies fighting Bern early in the game.

He is a close friend of [[Eliwood (Fire Emblem)|Eliwood]], and may marry one of [[Lyn_(fire_emblem)|Lyn]], [[Florina (Fire Emblem)|]], or [[farina_(fire_emblem)|Farina]] should they reach an A ranked support.

The head of the Lungmen Guard Department's Special Inspection Unit. During her time with the Department, she cracked down on crime, fought violent offenders, tracked down armed fugitives, and brought down international criminals. She also works at Rhodes Island, providing on-site tactical command.

She is the primary protagonist in the story [i]Episode 5: Necessary Solution[/i].

Her motif is based on a Chinese dragon.

Her [[voice actor]]s are [[Ishigami Shizuka|Shizuka Ishigami]] (Japanese), Jen Zhang (Mandarin), Bao Shaoye (Cantonese), Amy Lennox (English), and Chung Yu-joung (Korean). Her original art designer is [[yui (niikyouzou)|yui]], while her [b]After the Storm[/b] outfit is drawn by [[five-fall]].

title: phainon_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable [[Honkai: Star Rail]] character. A member of the [[Chrysos Heirs (honkai: star rail)|]]. Voiced by [[Hino Satoshi]] (regular) and [[Aihara Kotomi]] (young) in Japanese. 

He has [[short hair|short]] [[white hair]] with [[antenna hair|two ahoge]], [[blue eyes]], and a [[sun tattoo]] on the left side of his [[neck tattoo|neck]]. His outfit consists of a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white coat]] worn over a [[black shirt|black]] undershirt, a [[single glove|single]] [[fingerless gloves|fingerless]] [[black gloves|black glove]] on his left hand, [[black choker]], [[blue cape]], [[black pants]], [[tassel]]s on blue straps, and [[knee boots|knee-length]] [[black boots]].

title: rotom
body:
[[pokemon_(creature)|Pokémon]] #0479 in the National Pokédex.

A plasma-based creature with a whitish-blue [[aura]] of [[electricity]] that forms lightning bolt-shaped appendages. It has [[teeth]], and its [[blue eyes]] have a dividing line across them.

It has the ability to change its form and type by possessing an [[electric fan]], [[refrigerator]], [[microwave]], [[lawnmower]], or [[washing machine]].  Additionally, it can possess a [[pokedex|Pokédex]], [[smartphone]], [[computer]], [[drone]], or [[bicycle]]; these forms aid the Trainer but are not usable in battle.

Prior to Generation V, all of Rotom's forms were Electric/Ghost-type.

See [[Rotom (other)]] for fan works where Rotom is seen possessing other appliances.

Japanese name: [b]Rotom[/b]

title: judaism
body:
The first of the three Abrahamic religions and the first world religion to focus on only worshipping [[Yahweh|a single God]]. Originally centered around the Middle East, ancient Jews were expelled from their homeland by the Roman Empire and scattered across Europe, Asia, and Africa. As a result, Judaism in general is extremely decentralized in comparison to other religions. Its branches have historically referred to the geographic origin of said branch (Ashkenazi, Sephardic, etc.), though in the 20th Century it has started to take on branches of how closely they interpret ancient scripture (Orthodox, Reform, etc.).

Elements of Jewish mysticism are frequently used in Japanese media for symbolic effect, such as in [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]] or [[Final Fantasy VII]].

Use this tag for posts depicting clear-cut, significant reference to Judaism.

title: dew_drop
body: Tiny drops of water that form on cool surfaces at night, when atmospheric vapor condenses.

title: condensation
body:
Small drops of [[water]] that accumulate on surfaces colder than the surrounding air, such as on cold [[drinking_glass|drinking glasses]]. [[dew drop|Dew]] is a form of condensation usually found mornings after objects drop in temperature overnight. In freezing temperatures, condensation may take the form of [[frost]].

Condensation on glass surfaces such as [[window|windows]] and [[mirror|mirrors]] may produce a [[window fog]] effect (post #1579162). See the [[glass writing]] tag for text and symbols made on fogged glass with one's finger. 

Please don't confuse the appearance of condensation on glass with [[frosted glass]], where the glass itself is created to have a foggy appearance.

Contrast the condensation found on solid objects with various types of airborne water droplets:

* [[breath]]
* [[cloud]]
* [[contrail|contrail]]
* [[fog]] / mist
* [[steam]]

body:
A bowl-shaped plumbing fixture for washing hands or utensils. Usually provided with a water source (such as a [[faucet]], or water [[pump]]) and a drain. Bathroom sinks are almost always paired with [[mirror|mirrors]]. Sinks may be free-standing fixtures or they may be integrated into a [[counter]].

title: tarn
body:
A character from the [[Transformers]] science fiction franchise, first introduced in the [[The Transformers (Idw)|IDW comic series]].

[b]Tarn[/b] is an evil [[Decepticon]], a sentient [[alien]] [[robot]] that can transform into a futuristic alien [[tank]]. A fanatic to the Decepticon cause, to the point of wearing the faction's emblem as a face mask.

Motto: [i]"Doubt is the root of all failure...!!!".[/i]

title: kiryuu_keiki
body:
The main character [[Kawaikereba Hentai Demo Suki Ni Natte Kuremasu Ka?]]. 

A second-year high school student. A kind, friendly, and considerate guy who wants to finally start a relationship with a girl. He is in the calligraphy club with his senpai [[Tokihara Sayuki]]. He is trying to find the mysterious girl "Cinderella" who sent him a love letter along with her underwear.
[spoiler]Mysterious girl "Cinderella" turns out to be his non-sister [[Kiryuu Mizuha]][/spoiler]
